1. d4 { The Catalan is an opening system seen after 1.d4/2.c4, though other move orders are also possible. } 1... Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 { This is the starting position of the Catalan proper. } 4... Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O { This is the basic Catalan setup - kingside fianchetto, castle kingside, and pawns side by side in the centre on d4 and c4. } *


