1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 { The Queen's Gambit Accepted is the main opening where the Catalan setup is too slow. } (2... c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 { Here 4.g3 is still possible, but it entails a pawn sacrifice after 4...dxc4. Therefore, White may consider starting with } 4. Qc2 { , defending the c4-pawn, and only then playing the familiar g3/Bg2/0-0. } { [%cal Gg2g3,Gf1g2,Ge1g1] }) 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 { This is too slow when Black can quickly strike in the centre. } (4. e3 e6 5. Bxc4 { is better, with a normal Queen's Gambit Accepted main line after } 5... c5) 4... c5 5. Bg2 Nc6 { Black has early pressure against the White centre, and a move like 6.dxc5 would lose the right to castle after 6...Qxd1. } *


