[UTCTime "13:10:27"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Bg2 { An alternative move order, which is unlikely to make much difference, however. } 4... Be7 5. Nf3 O-O 6. O-O dxc4 7. Qc2 { White plays to regain his pawn. } 7... a6 (7... b5 { could lead to a nasty trap: } 8. a4 c6? 9. axb5 cxb5 10. Ng5 { wins at least a piece, as ...Nd5 fails to Qxh7 mate. }) (7... c6 8. Qxc4 b5 9. Qc2 Bb7 { was played many times in the 2018 FIDE Candidates, and this Meran-style system is one I've had amazing results with as Black in online blitz. } { [%cal Gb8d7,Gd8b6,Ga8c8,Gc6c5] }) 8. a4 { I like this move, preventing ...b5. } (8. Qxc4 b5 9. Qc2 Bb7 { gives Black a nice Meran-style setup with ...Nbd7 and ...c5, if unchallenged. }) 8... Bd7 { With ...b5 stopped, Black brings the bishop to the long diagonal another way. } 9. Qxc4 Bc6 { Now White can choose where to place his bishop and get his remaining pieces out in an attempt to use his central majority. In turn, Black can exploit the weak b4-square with ...a5/...Na6-b4, confident in the overall solidity of his position. } { [%csl Gb4][%cal Gc1f4,Gc1g5,Ga6a5,Gb8a6] } *


[Event "The Basic Catalan: Other Move Orders"]
[Date "2019.01.07"]
