[UTCTime "03:03:41"]

{ - It's usually good to have more choices than your opponent. This often allows you to control the situation against a smaller force to give up all your remaining pieces at once (a 'chain' of captures).

- Bishops are the worst pieces, as they can easily be forced into a 'capturing chain'.

- The same thing can happen to Rooks, but they are often the best piece to promote to in the endgame, due to their selective mobility.

- Queens can often escape capturing chains by threatening several pieces at once.

- One will usually promote to a King when trying to draw.

- Knights are quite slow and lack the ability to gain many tempo. They can also be forced into a chain of captures, though not as easily.

- Pawns should generally be advanced to acquire more space.

- A 'Queen capture race' is when each side captures as many pieces as possible with the Queen, to wipe out the opponent and stop them using their pieces.

- }
 *


