1. e4 e6 2. d3 d5 3. Nd2 { KIA (King's Indian Attack) - system opening, give the opponent a wide choice } { [%cal Gg2g3,Gg1f3,Gf1g2,Ge1g1] } 3... c5 4. g3 Nc6 5. Bg2 { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gg1f3,Gf8d6,Gg8e7] } 5... g6 { [%cal Gf8g7,Gg8e7] } (5... Nf6 6. Ngf3 Be7 7. O-O O-O 8. Re1 b5 9. e5 Nd7 { [%csl Ge7,Gg7] } 10. Nf1 { [%csl Gh7][%cal Gh2h4,Gf1h2,Gc1f4,Gf3g5,Gd1h5] } 10... Qc7 11. Bf4 Bb7 12. h4 Rfc8 13. h5 { [%csl Gf6,Gg5][%cal Gh5h6] } 13... h6 { [%cal Gh5h6] } 14. N1h2 { Standard attacking motifs (Fischer-Myagmasuren) } { [%csl Gh6][%cal Gh2g4,Gg4h6] }) 6. Ngf3 Bg7 7. O-O Nge7 8. Re1 O-O { [%cal Gc2c3,Ge4e5] } 9. Qe2?! (9. e5 Qc7 10. Qe2 g5) (9. c3 { [%csl Gc3,Gd4,Ge5,Gb2][%cal Ge4e5,Gd3d4] }) 9... b5 10. e5 a5 11. Nf1 { Kingside vs. queenside (KID) } { [%csl Gg8][%cal Gb5b4,Ga5a4,Gb4b3,Gh2h4,Gh4h5] } 11... Ba6 12. h4 b4 13. N1h2 { Neither side has touched the side of the board where they are weaker - this is why we're happy if Black plays ...g6 - f6 and h6 become weak } { [%csl Gg6,Gf7,Gh7,Ga2,Gb2,Gc2,Gh6,Gf6][%cal Yc1g5,Yh2g4,Ga5a4,Gb4b3] } (13. Bf4) 13... h6! (13... c4 14. Ng4 $13) 14. Bf4 Kh7 { [%csl Gg5,Gg4][%cal Ge2d2,Gh2g4,Gg4f6] } 15. Bh3?! { [%cal Yh3f5,Ge7f5,Gf5d4] } (15. Ng4 Nf5 16. Qd2 { Kasparov }) 15... c4 16. Kg2 { [%cal Gg1h1] } 16... Nf5 17. Bxf5 gxf5 18. g4 { Logical Decision Making by Ramesh
Black to play (P) } { [%cal Gg3g4] } 18... fxg4? (18... cxd3 19. cxd3 d4 { Kasparov }) (18... Ne7 { Kasparov } { We would prefer White to take first (on f5) rather than playing ...fxg4 } { [%cal Gg4f5,Ge7f5,Gh2g4] } 19. gxf5 Nxf5 { [%cal Gf5h4,Gb4b3] }) (18... Rg8!? { [%cal Gg8g2] } 19. gxf5 Bxe5+ { [%cal Gf4g3,Ge5b2] }) 19. Nxg4 { [%csl Gg4] } 19... Ne7 { Kasparov was a talented attacking player even in his youth (initiative) } { [%csl Ge7,Gf5,Gh2,Gg4][%cal Ge7f5] } (19... cxd3 20. cxd3 Ne7) 20. Bg5!! hxg5 (20... Rg8 21. Kh3 $40 { Kasparov }) 21. hxg5 { White has a big space advantage around the king (weaknesses around Black's king) } { [%csl Gf6,Ge5,Gg5][%cal Gg4f6,Ge1h1,Gh1h2,Ga1h1] } 21... Rh8 (21... cxd3 22. Qd2! { Kasparov }) (21... Nf5 22. Nf6+ Bxf6 23. exf6 { [%csl Gf6][%cal Ge1h1,Gh1h3,Ga1h1,Gf6e7,Gf6g7] }) 22. Nf6+ { [%cal Gg7f6,Gg5f6] } 22... Kg6 { [%csl Gf6,Gg5,Ge5][%cal Gf3h4] } (22... Bxf6 23. Rh1+ Kg8 24. gxf6 Ng6 25. Rxh8+ Kxh8 26. Rh1+ Kg8 27. Qe3 Qf8 28. Ng5 $18 { Kasparov }) 23. Rh1! Nf5 24. Rxh8 Bxh8 { Bring all the pieces into the attack } 25. Nd4 { [%cal Ge2h5] } (25. Rh1 $18 { [%cal Gf3h4,Ge2h5,Gh1h8] }) 25... Nxd4 (25... Bxf6 26. gxf6 Nh6 27. Rh1 $18) 26. Qh5+ { [%cal Gg6g7,Gh5h6] } 26... Kf5 27. g6+ Kf4 { [%cal Gh5g4,Gf4e5,Ge5d6] } 28. Re1 Bxf6 { White to play (P) } { [%csl Ga6,Gd4,Gf6] } 29. f3! { [%csl Rf4][%cal Rh5g4,Rg4f4] } 29... Nxf3 30. Qxf3+ Kg5 { Any move is fine as long you force a position that you know how to win } { [%cal Gf3g3] } 31. Qg3+ { [%cal Gg5h6,Gh6g7] } (31. Rh1! { [%cal Gf3h5,Gg5f4,Gh1f1] } 31... Kxg6 (31... fxg6 32. Qg3+ Kf5 33. Rf1#) 32. Qh5+ Kg7 33. Qh6+ Kg8 34. exf6 { [%csl Gh8] }) 31... Kh5 (31... Kh6 32. exf6 Qxf6 33. Rh1+ Kg7 34. Rh7+ Kg8 35. Rxf7 Qxf7 36. gxf7+ Kxf7 37. Qc7+ Kf6 38. Qc6 Ra7 39. Qb6 Ra8 40. Kf2 cxd3 41. cxd3 $18 { Kasparov }) 32. exf6 { 1-0 Black resigns. } { [%cal Re1h1] } 1-0


