1. c4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. g3 Nc6 4. Nf3 d6 5. Nc3 { The Catalan is often an annoying opening for players to face, but I've found the subsequent setup to be extremely effective in my own online games. } 5... Bd7 6. Bg2 Qc8 7. O-O h5?! (7... Bh3! { is the more accurate version of the 'Nakamura Variation', as I name it in my course 'Play 1...g6 Like Hikaru'. }) 8. h4! { Now the kingside attack comes to the end. Nakamura still won the game, but not because of the opening. } 8... Nh6 9. Bg5 Ng4 10. Rc1 f6 11. Bd2 e5 12. Nd5 Be6 13. Qc2 Kf7 14. dxe5 dxe5 15. b4 Nd8 16. b5 c6 17. Nc3 Bf8 18. Qa4 Bd7 19. Rfd1 a6 20. Qb3 Ne6 21. Ne4 Nc5 22. Nxc5 Bxc5 23. Be1 e4 24. Nd4 Re8 25. bxc6 bxc6 26. Rb1 f5 27. Qb7 Ra7 28. Qxc8 Rxc8 29. e3 Be7 30. Bf1 c5 31. Ne2 Ba4 32. Rdc1 Ne5 33. Nf4 Nf3+ 34. Kg2 g5 35. hxg5 Bxg5 36. Be2 Bxf4 37. exf4 h4 38. Bc3 Rd7 39. gxh4 Rg8+ 40. Kh3 Rg4 41. h5 Rd6 42. Rb7+ Kf8 43. Bxf3 Rd3 44. h6 Rxf3+ 45. Kh2 Rxf2+ 46. Kh3 Rf3+ 47. Kh2 Rh4+ 48. Kg2 Rfh3 49. Bg7+ Ke8 50. Rg1 Rd3 51. Rgb1 Rd2+ 52. Kg1 Rg4+ 53. Kf1 Rxf4+ 54. Kg1 Rg4+ 55. Kf1 e3 56. R7b2 Bc2 57. Rb8+ Kf7 58. Rf8+ Kg6 59. Rb6+ Kh5 { 0-1 Black wins. } 0-1


