1. d4 g6 2. Nf3 Bg7 3. e3 d6 4. Be2 Nd7 5. O-O e5 6. b3 Nh6 (6... e4 7. Nfd2 f5 { is perhaps the best way to use the Modern move order to our advantage, as I show in my 'Play 1...g6 Like Hikaru' course. }) 7. Bb2 (7. e4 { is the best move, but it's basically a Modern a tempo down for White, and with this weird b3 move included to boot. }) 7... O-O 8. c4 e4 9. Nfd2 Re8 10. Nc3 f5 11. d5 Nf7 { Black is already better here, even without White's next blunder. } 12. Nb5 Bxb2 { 0-1 Black wins. } 0-1


