1. d4 g6 2. Nf3 Bg7 3. g3 d6 4. Bg2 Bd7 5. O-O Qc8 6. Re1 { A common move among strong players, intending to meet ...Bh3 with Bh1 to keep the light-squared bishop. But I find it a bit imprecise. } (6. e4 { would be more to the point. }) 6... Bh3 (6... Nc6 7. e4 e5 8. d5 Nce7 9. c4 f5 10. Nc3 Nf6 { is also possible, playing a King's Indian but where we got in ...f5 and ...Nf6, as opposed to ...Nf6-d7, ...f5 and ...Nf6 (which would take 4 moves instead of 2). }) 7. Bh1 Nc6 8. e4 h5 9. d5 Ne5 10. Nxe5 Bxe5 11. Nd2 h4 12. Nc4 hxg3 13. hxg3 Bg4 14. Bf3 { Now Black gets a very strong attack on the White king. } (14. Qd3 { was correct. }) 14... Bxf3 (14... Nf6! 15. Nxe5 dxe5 { shows that our attack persists even without the dark-squared bishop. }) 15. Qxf3 Qh3 16. Qg2 Qh5 17. Nxe5 Qxe5 18. c3 Nf6 19. Bf4 Qh5 20. e5 g5 21. exf6 gxf4 22. Rxe7+ Kf8 23. g4 Qh4 24. Rae1 Qxf6 25. Qf3 Qxe7 26. Rxe7 Kxe7 27. Qxf4 a5 28. Qg5+ Kf8 29. Qf6 Rg8 30. f3 Re8 31. Kf2 b6 32. c4 Rg6 33. Qh4 Kg7 34. b3 f6 35. f4 Rh8 36. Qg3 Re8 37. Kf3 Kf7 38. f5 Rh6 39. g5 fxg5 40. Qxg5 Reh8 41. Ke3 Rh3+ 42. Kd2 Rh2+ 43. Kc1 Rg8 44. Qe3 Re8 45. Qg3 Ree2 46. Qg6+ Kf8 47. Qf6+ Ke8 48. Qg6+ Kd7 { 0-1 Black wins. } 0-1


