1. Nf3 g6 2. e4 Bg7 3. d4 d6 4. Nc3 Nf6 { Black transposes to the Pirc. } (4... a6 { is my recommendation in the 'Play 1...g6 Like Hikaru' course, intending either a 'Tiger's Modern' setup with ...b5, ...Nd7, ...Bb7 and ...c5, or in the case of } 5. a4 b6 { , a Hippo where White's setup with Nf3 and a4 eliminates White's best options against the Hippopotamus setup. }) 5. Be3 c6 6. a4 a5 { Black delays castling to take some of the sting out of the Qd2/Bh6 attacking plan. } 7. h3 Na6 8. Be2 O-O 9. O-O Nb4 { Now Black will follow with a dark-squared strategy. } 10. Re1 Qc7 11. Bf4 Nh5 12. Bh2 e5 { Black is doing fine, as the h2-bishop is a bit passive. } 13. Bc4 Qe7 14. Ne2 (14. Bb3 { first was better, in light of Black's next move. }) 14... d5! { [%c_effect d5;square;d5;type;GreatFind;persistent;true] } 15. Bb3 dxe4 16. Nxe5 Be6 17. Bxe6 Qxe6 18. g4 Nf6 19. Nf4 Qc8 20. f3 exf3 21. c3 f2+ 22. Kxf2 Nbd5 23. Nfd3 Nd7 24. Qb3 Nxe5 25. Bxe5 f5 26. g5 f4 27. Bxg7 Kxg7 28. Kg2 Qf5 29. Qxb7+ Kh8 30. Ne5 f3+ 31. Kf2 Rab8 { 0- } 0-1


