1. d4 d5 (1... Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 { Avrukh Catalan GM Repertoire books (2015) }) 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 (3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 { I was also thinking about playing
the Catalan but I haven't played it enough to be confident to play it in a
tournament game } { 1) You'll never feel 100% ready to play a new opening - Yermolinsky often will learn an opening by playing it
2) I write the ChessPublishing Queen's Gambit column }) 3... Nf6 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bg5 Be7 (5... c6) 6. e3 h6 7. Bh4 O-O 8. Bd3 Re8 { [%cal Gd1c2,Ge1c1,Gc7c5] } 9. Qc2?! (9. Nge2 { Was more accurate } 9... c6 10. O-O Nbd7 { May be able to dispense with Qc2 } { [%cal Gd1c2] } 11. f3) (9. Nf3) 9... c5! (9... c6 { is fine for
white when black has played ...h6 for no apparent reason } { Bh4-f2 keep the pieces on the board } { [%cal Gh7h6,Gg5h4,Gf6e4,Gf2f3,Gh4f2,Gg1e2] }) 10. dxc5 d4 (10... Nc6 11. Nge2 { was my intention avoiding a situation where ...d4 would hit so
hard and just trying to castle and get my king to safety } { [%cal Ge7c5,Gh4f6,Gc3d5] } (11. a3 d4 12. O-O-O (12. exd4?? Nxd4 $19) 12... dxc3 13. Bxf6 Bxf6 14. Bh7+ Kf8 15. Rxd8 cxb2+ 16. Kb1 Rxd8 17. Be4 Be6 $13 { After a bunch of computer moves I arrived at this
position which appears as very unclear }) 11... Nb4 (11... d4 12. Rd1) 12. Qd1 Nxd3+?! 13. Qxd3 $14 { was not a concern, this looks like quite a comfortable
play against the IQP } { [%cal Ge7c5] }) 11. exd4 { Chess is not checkers - we're not forced to capture and we should look for alternatives } { [%cal Ge8e1] } (11. O-O-O! { when there is some line that
goes: } 11... dxc3 12. Bxf6 cxb2+ 13. Bxb2 { [%csl Gc1] } 13... Qa5 14. Ne2 { [%cal Gb8a6,Ga6c5] } 14... Bxc5 { My initial thought
was that this was quite unclear but it seems like simplifications will unfold } (14... Qxa2?? 15. Bh7+ Kh8 16. Bxg7+) (14... Na6 15. Qc3 Qxc3+ 16. Nxc3 Nxc5) 15. Qc3 Qxc3+ 16. Nxc3 { White's pieces are slightly more harmonious (Nd5) }) 11... Qxd4 (11... Nc6 12. Nge2 Nxd4 13. Nxd4 Qxd4 { King in centre }) 12. Bg3 { Natural move } (12. Nf3! Bxc5+?! 13. Kf1! $16 { Bxf6/Ne4 - going a bit deeper } { [%cal Gh4f6,Gc3e4] }) 12... Nc6 13. Nge2 Qxc5 14. a3 { [%cal Gf6h5] } 14... Nh5?! (14... Be6 { [%cal Ga8d8] } 15. O-O Rad8 16. Nf4 Bc8 $10) 15. b4 Qg5 (15... Qb6 16. Nd5 Qd8 17. Rd1 { Was my intention }) 16. O-O Nxg3 17. hxg3 (17. Nxg3 { I didn't like
this as I lose control over d4 }) 17... Bg4 18. Rfe1 Rad8 { [%csl Ge7] } 19. Nf4 Bf8?! (19... Bf6 $10 { [%cal Gf6a1] }) 20. Bc4 Ne5 21. Bd5 Bf5 (21... Bc8 22. Ne4 $36) 22. Qb3 Bg6? 23. Bxb7 Nd3 24. Rxe8 Rxe8 25. Nxg6 Qxg6 { LPDO - Loose Pieces Drop Off - 50% of tactics are based on undefended pieces } { [%csl Gb7] } 26. Rd1? { With now the threat of Be4 but I missed simple tactic } { [%cal Gd3f2] } (26. Bd5 { Better opposite-coloured bishop - enough to win with best play }) 26... Qf5? { Fortunately
for me, my opponent was down to 3 minutes (while I was still on 40 minutes)
which probably was one of the factors to why he missed this. } (26... Nxf2! { [%cal Gg1f2,Gg6b6] }) 27. Qc2 Qd7 28. Be4 Nxb4 29. axb4 Qg4 30. Rd4 { He lost on time here but his
position is of course lost. } 1-0


