1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nf3 Bg7 4. g3 c6 5. Nc3 d5 6. cxd5 cxd5 { Gligoric - Catalan setup was a different kind of chess to anything else - keeping the initiative and keeping control } 7. Ne5!? (7. Bg2 Ne4 { I had a feeling he knew this but he didn't know Ne5 without Bg2 }) 7... O-O (7... Nfd7) 8. Bg2 { [%cal Ge1g1] } 8... Be6!? (8... e6 { [%cal Gb8c6] }) (8... b6!? 9. O-O Bb7 { ...e6/...Nbd7 - very flexible } { [%cal Ge7e6,Gb8d7] }) 9. O-O Nbd7 { Both Black bishops are a bit inept } { [%csl Ge6,Gd7,Gf6,Gg7] } 10. Bf4 (10. Nd3 { [%csl Gg2,Ge6][%cal Gd3f4] } 10... Nb6 11. Nc5 Qc8 12. Bf4 Bh3 13. Rc1 $14 { - even though in theory the g2-bishop is our 'good' bishop, we're very happy to have it traded off. Playing with the pieces } { [%cal Gc3a4,Gd1b3] }) 10... Nxe5 11. Bxe5 (11. dxe5 Ng4 12. Nxd5 Nxe5 { I
probably should've went for this where I have slightly more active pieces } 13. Qb3 $14 { [%csl Gd8][%cal Gf8e8,Gb3b7,Ga8b8] } 13... b6 14. Rfd1 { [%csl Gd8] }) 11... Qd7 12. e3 (12. Bxf6 Bxf6 { [%cal Ge2e3] } 13. e3 { Be6/Bf6 - positional bind } { [%csl Gf6,Ge6][%cal Ge6h3,Gc3d5,Gd5f6] } 13... Bg7 { [%cal Gf7f6,Ge6f7,Ge7e6] } 14. Qb3 Rfd8 15. Rfc1 { White's position is easier } { [%cal Gc3a4,Ga4c5] }) 12... Rfd8 { [%cal Ge5f6] } 13. Qb3 (13. Bxf6 exf6 { Bad structure } { [%csl Gd5] } 14. Qb3 { [%cal Gf1c1] } 14... Bf8) 13... Ne4 14. Nxe4? (14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. Nxe4 (15. Rfc1 Rac8) 15... dxe4 16. Qb4 Bd5 17. Rfc1 Rac8 $10) 14... dxe4 15. Qb4 f6 { I honestly
don't know how I missed this idea } 16. d5 Bxd5 17. Bc3 { -0.6 } { [%csl Ge4,Ge7] } 17... a5 18. Qc5 Qc6 { I
missed this but then somehow I thought that I could take on e7 as after ...Rd7
I have some kind of escape but somehow completely overlooked the simple ...Re8 } 19. Qxe7 { Candidate moves - also for the opponent - what are all the different forcing options? } 19... Re8 { 0-1 White resigns. } { Tal, Adhiban, Mamedyarov, Kasparov, Wei Yi, Stein, young Radjabov, young Carlsen, Vachier Lagrave
Looks positional but is actually very tricky and tactical - Aronian } (19... Rd7 20. Qa3 Bf8 21. b4) 0-1


