1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. c3 Nf6 4. Be2 { This side system isn't as harmless as it
looks - White is aiming for building up a strong pawns centre. } 4... g6 5. O-O Bg7 6. Bb5+ Nc6 { Sergey chooses a relatively rare theoretical continuation. } (6... Bd7 { is much more popular. There are some practical tests: } 7. Bxd7+ Qxd7 (7... Nbxd7 8. Re1 O-O 9. d4 cxd4 10. cxd4 d5 11. e5 Ne4 12. Nbd2 Nxd2 13. Bxd2 Qb6 14. Re3 Rac8 15. h4 $14 { Sagalchik,G (2525)-Serper,G (2535) New York 1996 }) 8. Re1 O-O 9. d4 Na6 10. d5 c4 11. Nbd2 Nc5 $132 { Adams,M (2685)-Anand,V (2735)
Dortmund 1996 }) 7. d4 Qb6 (7... O-O 8. d5 Nb8 9. Re1 Bg4 10. Nbd2 Nbd7 11. h3 Bxf3 12. Nxf3 a6 13. Bf1 b5 14. Bf4 $14 { Chadaev,N (2580)-Gelfand,B (2738)
Astana 2012 }) (7... Bd7 8. d5 Ne5 9. Bxd7+ Nfxd7 10. Nxe5 Nxe5 11. a4 O-O 12. Bf4 Qb6 13. Qe2 c4 14. Bxe5 Bxe5 15. a5 Qb3 16. Na3 $14 { Lombardy,W - Hort,V
Zagreb 1969 }) 8. Ba4 (8. Na3 { was admitted by } 8... cxd4 9. cxd4 d5! { in Rasik,V (2516)-Zhigalko,A
(2601) Czechia 2013 }) 8... cxd4 9. cxd4 O-O 10. d5 { This position was seen
only in 1 preceding game! } 10... Nb8 $146 { This move looks somewhat artificial, but
the knight is heading to c5 or e5. } (10... Na5 11. Nc3 (11. Re1 Bg4 12. Nbd2 Rfc8 13. h3 Bd7 14. Bc2 e6 $132) 11... Bg4 12. h3 Bxf3 13. Qxf3 Rac8 14. Qe2 Nc4 { was fine for Black in Palit,S (2421)-Gopal,G (2558) Kolkata 2014 }) 11. Nc3 (11. Re1 Bg4 12. Nbd2 Qc7 13. h3 Bd7 14. Bc2 Rc8 15. Bb1 a5 $132) 11... Bg4 12. h3 Bxf3 13. Qxf3 Nbd7 14. Rb1 (14. Be3 Qxb2 15. Rfc1 { only leads to
simplifications: } 15... Qa3 16. Rab1 Nc5 17. Bxc5 Qxc5 18. Rxb7 Nxe4! 19. Qxe4 Bxc3 20. Qf3 Qa3) 14... Rfc8 { Black has completed a harmonious setup. The
position is closed yet, so White's bishops do not guarantee White any
advantage. } 15. Bc2 Ne5 (15... a6!? 16. Qe2 Qa5 17. Bd2 Ne5 $132) 16. Qe2 Nfd7 17. Bg5 { The Pe7 isn't really hanging, but the presense of White's bishop on
g5 is somewhat annoying. } 17... h6 (17... Bf6!? 18. Bxf6 Nxf6 19. Kh2 Nc4 20. Bd3 Qd4 { The activity of Black's pieces doesn't
allow to develop a serious attack on the kingside. }) 18. Bh4 g5 { A
double-edged decision. Black manages to secure the Ne5, but this advance
exposes the light squares around the king. } 19. Bg3 Qa6 (19... Ng6!? 20. Rfc1 Be5 21. Bxe5 Ndxe5 22. g3 Rc4 $132) 20. Qd1 Rc4? { The first cause of Sergey's troubles! } (20... Nc4 21. Bd3 Qb6 (21... Nc5 22. Be2 Bxc3 23. bxc3 Qxa2 24. Ra1 Qb3 25. Qd4 { looks risky for a
human eye }) 22. Qe2 Nde5 $132) 21. Kh1 { This is the point! Most of Black's
pieces are on the queenside, so White manages to develop a powerful attack now. } 21... Rac8 22. f4 gxf4 23. Bxf4 Qb6 { The queen is coming into defence, but it
takes a long time... } 24. Qh5 Nf6 (24... Qd8 25. Bxh6 Nf6 26. Qh4 Ng6 27. Qg5 Qf8 28. Bxg7 Qxg7 29. Rf5 $16) 25. Qf5 Qd8 (25... Ng6 26. Bd2 Qd8 27. Bb3 R4c7 28. Be3 $16) 26. Bb3 Rd4 27. Bxe5 dxe5 { As it often happens, the presense of bishops of different
colours favours the attacking side! } 28. Rbd1 (28. Rbc1!? Qd7 29. Qxd7 Nxd7 30. Ne2 Rxc1 31. Rxc1 Rd2 (31... Rxe4 32. Ng3 Rf4 33. Rc7 $36) 32. Rc8+ Bf8 33. Ng3 $36 { Even though liquadating into the endgame is
Black's undisputable achievement, the position is still very unpleasant. }) 28... Qd7 29. Qf3 Rb4 (29... Rxd1 30. Qxd1 b5 31. Qd3 a6 32. Ne2 $36 { it wouldn't easy to find a
constructive defenseve plan. }) 30. Rd2! { The rook would be very useful along
2nd rank. } 30... Rf8 31. g4! { As usual, World Champion's play is very energetic
and impressive. } 31... a5? { Black cannot afford wasting a tempo for
counter-attacking measures. } (31... Nh7 32. h4 Rb6 33. Rg1 Rf6 34. Qg3 $16 { White still has to find a way to make
progress. }) 32. Rg2 Nh7 33. h4 { Now White's attack lasts itself. } 33... Rb6 34. g5 Kh8 (34... Rg6 35. Rfg1 Kh8 36. Ba4 Qc8 37. Rh2 $18 { Black would
be almost paralysed. }) 35. Rfg1 f5 { A desperate attempt to complicate the
matters. } 36. Qh3 Rb4 37. gxh6 Bxh6 { The king is too exposed, so White has
many winning ways now. } 38. Qg3 (38. Rg6 Bf4 39. Qg2 $18 (39. d6 $18)) 38... Nf6 39. Qg6 Ng4 40. Rxg4 { 1-0 Black resigns. } 1-0


