{ 1. How to create and occupy open files with rooks/queens piled together, and get to the opponents' 7th rank? How to pick which file to open? e.g. the timing of f6 break in French and f file pawn break in Ruy Lopez white (not sure if thats the common one)
2. We had a look at alekhine's gun game, (the first game alekhine played) but not in detail, Lucas is quite interested in how this works.

3. How to evaluate a mid game position in general? I assume the key things we look at are: who has the key to open file, pawn structure, strong squares, king safely and centre. Most beginners like Lucas find it hard to evaluate, i.e. don't know what to do? or they may know opponent's weakness but can't tackle them.

4. In particular, it will be good if you could go through some fundamental understanding for pawn structure and weaknesses, e.g. what is a weak pawn and what both sides should do?

5. Lastly, he lost a game last weekend in Ruy Lopez, opponents played Berlin defense, he's down a couple pawns from early on, but played good in end game, unfortunately he ran out of time and it was the only loss in last weekend's tournaments, I didn't see the game but not sure if there's any trick there in Berlin defense so feel like he may need some refresh

6. Last week's homework }
 *


