1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6. Be2 e5 7. O-O Nc6 8. d5 Ne7 { Both sides are going to play on the side of the board where they're stronger.
If you move pawns on the side where you're weaker - make it easier for them to open the position, create weaknesses that they can attack } { [%cal Gc4c5,Gf7f5] } 9. Ne1 Nd7 { [%cal Gf7f5] } (9... a5 10. Nd3 b6 { Play on the side of the board where you have more space (create counterplay on the flank where you're worse) } { [%csl Gd5,Ge6,Gc6][%cal Gb2b3,Ga2a3,Gb3b4,Gc4c5,Gc5b6,Gc5d6,Gb4a5] }) (9... c6 { [%cal Gc6d5,Gc4d5,Gb7b5,Gb5b4] }) *


