have played 3 games so far with Veselin leading 2-1 }) 6... e6 7. Bb3 { [%csl Ge6][%cal Gf2f4,Gf4f5,Gf5e6,Gb3g8] } 7... Nbd7 (7... b5) 8. Bg5 (8. f4 Nc5 { [%cal Gf6e4,Gc5b3] }) 8... Qa5 9. Bxf6 Nxf6 10. O-O Be7 { The first real surprise } { Scheveningen structure } (10... Nd7 { was played. }) 11. f4 Qc5 { [%cal Ge6e5,Gc5g1] } 12. Kh1 b5 { All these moves are logical
and do not require any comments. } { Black has all the long-term advantages (bishop pair and central majority) } { [%csl Ge8] } 13. a3 (13. f5 e5 14. Nf3 Bb7 15. Qd3 (15. Nd5 Nxd5 16. Bxd5 Bxd5 17. exd5 O-O { Hole is not necessarily a real weakness } { [%cal Ge5e4,Ge7f6] }) 15... b4 (15... O-O!?) 16. Nd5 Bxd5 17. Bxd5 Nxd5 18. exd5 O-O 19. Nd2 Rac8 20. Rac1 $13 { was also worth considering, but I was sure that my opponent
was prepared for this. }) 13... Bb7 { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gf4f5,Ge6e5] } (13... O-O? 14. f5 e5 15. Nd5! Ra7 16. Nxf6+ Bxf6 17. Ne2 $16) 14. Qd3 (14. Bxe6? fxe6 15. Nxe6 Qc4 16. Nxg7+ Kf7 17. Nf5 Bxe4 $17) 14... g6!? { A very ambitious move, typical for Topalov. } (14... O-O { [%csl Gd3][%cal Gf8d8,Gd8d3] } 15. Rae1 Rfd8 $13) (14... Kf8 15. Bxe6 fxe6 16. Nxe6+ { [%csl Ge8] } 16... Kf7 17. Nxc5 dxc5) 15. f5!? { A no less ambitious move after which the board is on fire. } { [%cal Gf5g6,Gf5e6] } (15. Rae1 O-O-O $13 { was probably the idea of 14...g6 } 16. Bxe6+ fxe6 17. Nxe6 Qc6 18. Nxd8 Bxd8 $15 { It's hard for White to activate his rooks & the b7-bishop is very strong. } { [%csl Ge4,Gf4,Ge1,Gd8,Gb7][%cal Gb6g1,Gc4e6,Gd8b6] }) 15... gxf5 16. Nxf5! { The only way to justify the previous move. } (16. exf5? e5 $17 { is a
positional nightmare for White. } { [%cal Gd6d5,Ge5e4] }) 16... exf5 17. Rxf5 d5! { Extra material can be like ballast in a hot air balloon } { [%cal Gd6d5] } (17... Ng4?! { did not cross my mind during the game, but it
seems insufficient in view of } { [%cal Gf5c5,Gg4f2] } 18. Bxf7+ Kd8 19. Qg3 { [%cal Gg4e5] } 19... Ne5 20. Rd1 { with a
strong initiative to White. } 20... Kc7 21. Qg7 { [%csl Gc7][%cal Gf7h5,Gc7b6] } 21... Kb6 22. a4 b4 { [%cal Ga4a5] } 23. Nd5+ Bxd5 24. Bxd5 Rae8 { [%cal Ge8e7] } 25. c3) (17... Qb6 18. Raf1 { [%csl Gf6][%cal Gf1f7] } 18... Nd7 19. Bxf7+ { [%cal Gf7e8] }) 18. exd5!? (18. Nxd5 Nxd5 19. Bxd5 Bxd5 20. exd5 { was suggested by Topalov after the game, but while it is probably sufficient
for maintaining the balance, it still looks quite tame to me. }) 18... Qd6! { A good, human move. } { [%csl Gc3,Gb3,Gd3][%cal Gb3d5,Gc3d5,Ge8c8] } (18... Rg8 19. Re1! (19. Raf1 Rg6 20. Ne4 Nxe4 21. Qxe4 O-O-O 22. Rxf7 Bd6 { with unclear
play. }) 19... Kd8! (19... Kf8 20. Qf1! Qb6 (20... Kg7 21. Rxf6 Bxf6 22. Qxf6+ Kxf6 23. Ne4+ $16) 21. Ne4 $36) 20. Qf1! Qd6 21. Rxe7 Kxe7 22. Rxf6 Qxf6 23. d6+ Qxd6 24. Qxf7+ Kd8 25. Qxg8+ Kc7 26. Qf7+ { with perpetual. }) 19. Raf1 { When we're defending, we're not limited to passive defence - we can and should look for the right moment to counterattack } 19... Ng4! 20. Qh3 { [%csl Gg4][%cal Gh3h2] } (20. R1f4 Nh6! (20... Rg8? 21. Qe2 { is bad for Black. }) 21. Ne4 Nxf5 22. Nxd6+ Nxd6 23. Qe3 $13 { it was not clear to me if White has an edge here. }) 20... Rg8! { [%cal Gf5f7] } (20... h5 21. Ne4 Qh6 22. Rxf7 $16) 21. Ne4?! { A move made 'by hand'
which spoils an interesting game. } { Black to play (exercise) } { [%csl Gd6] } (21. Rxf7 O-O-O 22. R1f4 (22. Qxh7 Nxh2 23. Qxh2 Rh8 24. Rh7) 22... h5 23. Qxh5 Ne5 24. Ne4 Nxf7 25. Nxd6+ Nxd6 $13 { but in timetrouble I would like to
play Black in such a position, alltough the engines give a clear edge to White. } { Pieces are quite strong vs. queen when they are all defended (in a chain) } { [%csl Gd6,Ge7,Gd8,Gh5,Gc2,Gb7,Gg8][%cal Ge7g5] } 26. c3 (26. g3 Bg5 27. a4 Rg7 28. c3 Rdg8 29. c4 Bxf4 30. gxf4 Rg1#) 26... Rh8 { [%cal Gg7g5] } 27. Qg4+ { [%cal Gd8g8] } 27... Kb8 28. Rf5 Bc8 { [%cal Gc8g4] }) 21... Qh6! { [%csl Gh3,Gh6][%cal Gh3h6] } (21... Qg6 22. d6 Ne3 { [%cal Gb3f7] }) 22. Qxh6? (22. Re1! Qxh3 23. gxh3 Nh6 24. Re5 Kd8 25. Rxe7 Kxe7 26. Nc5+ Kf8 27. Nxb7 { would have given some saving
chances to White. }) (22. d6 Qxh3 { [%cal Gg4e3,Gg2h3] }) 22... Nxh6 $17 23. Re5 (23. d6 Nxf5 24. dxe7 Nxe7 25. Bxf7+ Kd7 26. Bxg8 Bxe4 27. Re1 Rxg8 28. Rxe4 Rf8 29. c4 Rf1#) 23... Kf8 { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gd5d6] } 24. h3?! (24. Rh5 Rg6 25. Rxh6 Rxh6 26. d6 f6 27. dxe7+ Kxe7 { but Black is close to winning
anyway. }) (24. d6 Bd8 { [%cal Gb7g2,Gg8g2] }) 24... Rg6 25. g4 Re8 26. Re1 Ng8 27. Nc5 Ba8 28. g5? Rd8 { 0-1 White resigns. } { [%cal Gc5e4,Ge7d6] } 29. Ne4 Bd6 30. Nxd6 Rdxd6 (30... Rgxd6 { [%csl Gd5] } 31. Rd1 Ne7 { [%csl Gd5] } 32. c4 bxc4 33. Bxc4 Nxd5 34. Bxd5 Bxd5+ 35. Rexd5 Rxd5 36. Rxd5 Rxd5 37. Kg2 Rd4 38. Kg3 Rg4+ 39. Kxg4 a5 40. b4 axb4 41. axb4 Ke8 42. b5 Kd8 43. b6 Kc8 44. b7+ Kxb7 45. Kf5 Kc6 46. Kf6 Kd5 47. Kxf7 Ke4 48. h4 Kf3 49. h5 Kg4 50. g6 h6 51. g7 Kxh5 52. g8=Q Kh4 53. Qh7 Kh5 54. Kf6 Kg4) 31. Re8+ 0-1


