{ there's not much theory behind this move, as there are several lines that have been played only a few times }
1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Nf3 dxc4 5. Bg2 Nbd7 { Old move, no top Grandmaster plays this, doesn't provide black with enough activity and fighting chances, the move itself isn't bad, it just isn't good enough. White has 3 options } 6. O-O { Playing in the catalan style, black has several options } { [%cal Gc7c5,Gf8e7,Gd7b6,Rc7c6,Ra7a6,Ba8b8,Bb7b5] } (6. Qa4 { will lead into early Qa4 lines transposition } { [%cal Ga4c4] } 6... a6 7. Nc3 (7. Qxc4 b5 { looks like extremely good semislav for black } { [%cal Gf8c5,Gd7c5] } 8. Qc6 { probably better than Qc2 } (8. Qc2 Bb7 9. O-O c5 { black has absolutely no issues } 10. a4 (10. dxc5 Bxc5 11. Nc3))) 7... b5 8. Nxb5) (6. Nbd2 Nb6 7. Nxc4 Nxc4 8. Qa4+ Bd7 9. Qxc4 { this is just equal } 9... Bc6 { that bishop is going to be great there } 10. O-O Be7 11. Bg5 O-O 12. Rac1 Rc8 13. Rfd1 { just an equal position, not good to play for an advantage with white } { [%cal Gd8d6,Gd6d5] }) 6... Be7 (6... a6 7. a4 Rb8 8. a5 Bd6 9. Nbd2 b5 10. axb6 Nxb6 11. Nxc4 Nxc4 12. Qa4+ Bd7 13. Qxc4 { black has a big weakness on a6 } { [%csl Ga6] }) (6... c6 7. a4 a5 (7... Bb4 8. Qc2 (8. Nbd2 Bxd2 (8... c3 9. bxc3 Bxc3 10. Ba3 Bxa1) 9. Nxd2 O-O 10. Nxc4)) 8. Qc2 Nb6 9. Nbd2 { white is going to get his pawn back } 9... Be7 10. Nxc4 Nxc4 11. Qxc4 { whose squares are weaker? }) (6... Nb6 7. Nbd2 c5 8. Nxc4 Nxc4 9. Qa4+ Bd7 10. Qxc4 b5 11. Qc2 Rc8 12. dxc5 Bxc5 13. Qb3) (6... Rb8 7. a4 b5 (7... b6 8. Nbd2 Ba6 9. Qc2 c3 (9... c5 10. Nxc4 Bxc4 11. Qxc4)) (7... a5 8. Nbd2 Nb6 9. Qc2 Be7 10. Nxc4 Nxc4 11. Qxc4 { [%csl Ga5] }) (7... a6 8. a5 b5 (8... Bd6 9. Nbd2 b5 10. axb6 cxb6 (10... Nxb6 { white doesnt have to take on c4, white has a lot of options and its easier for him to proceed } { [%cal Gf3e5,Gd1c2,Gb2b3,Ge2e4,Gd2c4] } 11. Nxc4 (11. b3) (11. Qc2) (11. Ne5) (11. e4 Be7 12. Ne5 { [%cal Ge5c6,Gd2c4,Gd1h5] }) 11... Nxc4 12. Qa4+ Bd7 13. Qxc4 { [%cal Gd7b5] } 13... Bb5 14. Qc2) 11. Nxc4 Bc7 12. Bd2 { slighting weaker than b2 } { [%csl Gb6,Ga6] }) 9. axb6 { [%cal Gc7b6,Gb6b5] } 9... Rxb6 (9... cxb6 10. Bf4 Rb7 (10... Ra8 11. Ne5 { embarassing } 11... Ra7 (11... Nd5 12. Nxc4) (11... Nxe5 12. Bxa8) 12. Nc6) 11. Rxa6) 10. Nbd2) 8. axb5 Rxb5 9. Rxa7) (6... c5 7. Na3 (7. dxc5 { terrible move } 7... Bxc5 8. Qc2 Qc7 9. Qxc4 Bxf2+) 7... Nb6 8. Nxc4 Nxc4 9. Qa4+ Bd7 10. Qxc4 b5 { [%csl Gd7,Gf8] } 11. Qc2 Rc8 12. Bg5 { there are only 4 games in the GM database and its 4 wins for white } (12. dxc5 Bxc5 13. Qb3 { not too many issues for black } 13... O-O 14. Ne5 Be8 (14... b4 15. Rd1 Qe7 16. Bg5) (14... Qb6 15. Bg5 Rfd8 16. Qf3 Be7 17. Nxd7 Rxd7 18. Rfc1) 15. Bf4) 12... Be7 (12... cxd4 13. Qd3 Bc5 14. Nxd4 a6 15. Rac1 h6 16. Bf4) (12... h6 13. Bxf6 gxf6 14. Rfd1 Qb6 15. d5) 13. dxc5 Rxc5 14. Qb3 O-O 15. Be3) 7. Nbd2 Nb6 8. Qc2 O-O 9. Nxc4 Nxc4 10. Qxc4 c6 { looks like a bad version of the semi slav } *


