1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 c5 6. O-O Nc6 7. Qa4 { ambitious } { [%cal Ga4e8,Gf3e5] } (7. dxc5 Qxd1 8. Rxd1 { not bad }) 7... Bd7 (7... cxd4 8. Nxd4 Qxd4 9. Bxc6+ Bd7 (9... bxc6 10. Qxc6+ { [%cal Gc6a8] }) 10. Rd1 (10. Bxd7+ Qxd7 11. Qxc4 Be7 { black is really fine here }) 10... Bxc6 (10... Qxd1+ 11. Qxd1 Bxc6 12. Nd2 { people tried to hold this position as black, being down a queen, but it turns out white can win the pawn back and then has a free roll to try and win the game } 12... b5 13. a4 Be7 14. axb5 Bxb5 15. Nxc4 Bxc4 16. Qa4+) 11. Qxc6+ bxc6 12. Rxd4 { white has a really nice endgame advantage } 12... c5 13. Rxc4 Be7 14. Nd2 O-O 15. Nb3 Nd5 16. Bd2 { [%csl Ga5][%cal Ga1c1] } 16... Nb6 17. Rc2 c4 18. Na5 { renewing the threads and eventually the pawn will fall } { [%cal Ga5c4] }) 8. Qxc4 b5 { kind of concession, because pawns don't move backwards } (8... cxd4 9. Nxd4 Rc8 10. Nc3 { natural development } 10... Nxd4 11. Qxd4 Bc5 { with a tempo } 12. Qh4 { black has to sac a pawn } 12... O-O (12... Bc6 { turns out white is much better here } 13. Rd1 Qb6 14. Bxc6+ Rxc6 15. Bh6 { BANG } 15... Bf8 (15... O-O { can't castle } 16. Bxg7 Kxg7 17. Qg5+ Kh8 18. Qxf6+) 16. Rd3 Qxb2 17. Rad1 Rxc3 18. Rd8+ Ke7 19. R1d7#) 13. Bxb7 Rb8 14. Bf3 { GM Vladimir Kramnik vs GM Arkadij Naiditsch } 14... Rb4 { black is much better mobilized, but there's no way to prove it, because white's position has no weaknesses } 15. Qg5 Bd4 16. Qd2 Qc7 17. Nd1 { [%cal Gd1b2] } 17... Rfb8 18. a3 Ra4 19. Ne3) 9. Qc3 b4 (9... cxd4 10. Nxd4 Nxd4 11. Qxd4 Rc8 12. Bf4 Bc5 13. Qd3 Qb6 14. Nd2 { GM Fabiano Caruana vs GM Arkadij Naiditsch } 14... O-O { if black had one more move and played Rd8, he would qualize, but white now has } 15. Ne4 { [%csl Gf6,Gd7,Gc5] } 15... Nxe4 16. Bxe4 { [%cal Gd3d7,Ge4h7] }) 10. Qd3 Rc8 11. dxc5 Bxc5 12. Be3 Bxe3 13. Qxe3 O-O 14. Nbd2 { c5, c4, a7 is weak, the knight finds a square on b3 taking away a5 and c5 and pawns don't move backwards, after white puts a rook on the c file, and knight on e5 activating the g2 bishop which gets really strong and white harmonizes, it will be really felt that the pawns are really weak } { [%csl Gc4,Gc5,Ga7][%cal Gd2b3] } *


