1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Nf3 Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O dxc4 7. Qc2 a6 8. a4 Bd7 { [%csl Rb4][%cal Gb8a6,Ga6b4] } 9. Rd1 { gives a very good chance getting a large advantage } (9. Qxc4 { leading into two lines where black can equalize } 9... Bc6 10. Bf4 (10. Bg5)) (9. Ne5 Bc6 10. Nxc6 Nxc6 11. e3 Na5 { [%cal Ga5c4] } 12. Nd2 c5 13. dxc5 Rc8 { black is qualizing } { [%csl Gc5][%cal Gc8c2] }) (9. Nc3 Nc6 { white would like to recapture but is now blocked } { [%cal Gc6b4,Gc6a5,Gc2c4] }) 9... Bc6 { now that the bishop has gone to c6 (Nc6 would be met with Qxc4) we can play Nc3 } 10. Nc3 { with a plan to play e4 and the bishop is very awkwardly placed } { [%cal Ge2e4,Rd1d8,Bf3e5,Bd4d5] } 10... a5 { [%cal Gb8a6,Ga6b4] } (10... Nbd7 { could instead try } 11. e4 b5 { trying to hold on onto the extra pawn, but white strikes in the centre immediately } 12. d5 exd5 13. e5 { exposes the lack of space } 13... Nc5 { could try giving up a piece but there's not enough compensation } (13... Ne4 14. Nxd5 Bxd5 15. Rxd5 Nec5 16. axb5 { black cannot take back, because } 16... axb5 17. Rxa8 Qxa8 18. Rxd7 Nxd7 19. Ng5 { [%cal Gg2a8,Gc2h7] }) 14. Nd4 Bb7 15. exf6 Bxf6 16. axb5 axb5 17. Rxa8 Qxa8 18. Ncxb5 c6 19. Nd6) (10... Nd5 11. e4 Nxc3 12. bxc3 b5 { trying to defend the pawn on c4 } 13. Ne5 Bb7 14. Rb1 { [%cal Ge5c4,Gb1b7] }) (10... Bxf3 { very hard to find, the best defense } 11. Bxf3 Nc6 { white has to make a consession } 12. Bxc6 (12. e3 { wont work beacause of } 12... Na5 { [%cal Ga5c4] }) 12... bxc6 13. a5 { with the idea of bringing the rook up and capturing this way } { [%csl Gc6,Gc7][%cal Ga1a4,Ga4c4] } 13... Nd5 { forcing us to change plan } (13... Rb8 14. Ra4 Rb4 15. Na2 Rxa4 16. Qxa4 Qb8 17. Qxc4 Qb5 18. Qxb5 cxb5 19. Be3 { and now we try to use blacks weaknesses on the queenside } 19... Nd5 20. Rc1 Rd8 21. Rc6 Rd6 22. Rc2 { [%csl Ra6,Rb4,Rc5,Rc7,Re5][%cal Ga2c1,Gc1d3] }) 14. Na4 Qb8 15. Qxc4 (15. Bd2 Qb5 16. Rdc1 { [%csl Gc6,Gc7][%cal Gc2c4] }) 15... Qb5 { hard t omeet }) (10... Bb4 11. Bg5 h6 (11... Nbd7 12. d5 exd5 13. Nxd5 Bxd5 14. Rxd5 Qe7 15. Bh3) 12. Bxf6 Qxf6 13. Na2 { with the idea of playing Qxc4 Nc3 and playing e4, taking space in the centre } { [%cal Gc2c4,Ga2c3,Ge2e4] }) 11. e4 { planning to play Na6 Nb4 } { [%cal Gb8a6,Ga6b4] } 11... Na6 12. Ne5 Nb4 13. Qe2 { white has managed to keep all the pieces on the board while managing to keep a very strong centre with a powerful pawn duo, because of the piece keeping the space advantage will make be felt very heavily } 13... h6 14. Be3 Qc8 15. Rd2 Rd8 16. Rad1 Be8 17. Nxc4 { now that all pieces are in the game it's time to recapture on c4 } 17... Ra6 18. Bh3 { [%cal Gh3c8,Gd4d5] } 18... Qb8 19. Bf4 { [%cal Gf4b8,Gc3b5,Gb5c7] } 19... g5 { weakening his king } { [%csl Gg8,Gg5] } 20. Be3 { [%cal Gf2f4] } 20... b5 21. Ne5 bxa4 22. f4 Nh7 23. Rf1 f6 24. Nc4 Kg7 25. d5 { finally opening up the position } 25... exd5 26. exd5 Bf7 27. Bd4 Re8 28. Bd7 Nxd5 29. Nxd5 Bxd5 30. Ne3 { [%cal Ge3f5] } 30... Re6 31. Bxe8 Qxe8 32. Nxd5 Rxe2 33. Rxe2 { with overwhelming material advantage } { [%cal Ge2e8] } *


[Event "A guide to Catalan: 4... Bb4+"]
