would react in a situation that was unfamiliar to me. } (10... cxd4 { was played. }) 11. Bg5! { Botvnnik:An unpleasant
replyfor Black. } 11... Qb6 12. Be4 Bb7 (12... Ra7 13. d5) 13. Bxb7 Qxb7 14. O-O $16 { [#] } 14... h5 (14... h6 15. Bh4 b4 16. Na4 cxd4 17. Qxd4 g5 18. Qxg4 gxh4 19. Rfe1 $16) 15. d5 { Botvinnik: When the opponent's king is caught in the centre, one
can without fear sacrifice a pawn for an attack. } 15... Ndxe5 16. Nxe5 Nxe5 17. dxe6 f6 { Botvinnik: Black avoids capturing the e6 pawn, which will now securely
block the e.line. } 18. Qe2 Be7 19. Rad1 $18 { [#] } 19... h4 (19... c4 20. Nd5 Nd3 (20... fxg5 21. Qxe5 O-O 22. Qe4 Ra7 23. Rfe1 $18) 21. Qe4 $18) (19... O-O 20. Bf4 Qc6 21. Bxe5 fxe5 22. Nd5 Rae8 23. Qe4 Qxe6 24. Nc7 $18) 20. f4 $18 h3 21. fxe5 Qxg2+ 22. Qxg2 hxg2 { [#] } 23. Kxg2? $16 (23. Rxf6! { Found by Komodo 11 } 23... Bxf6 24. exf6 gxf6 25. Bxf6 $18) 23... fxg5 { [#] } 24. Rf7 $16 (24. Nd5 $18 Ra7 25. Ne3 Rh6 (25... g6 26. Ng4 $18) 26. Nf5 Rg6 27. Rfe1 c4 28. Rd6 $18) 24... Rh6 25. Rxe7+ (25. Rxg7 Kf8 26. Rf7+ Ke8 27. Nd5 Rxe6 28. Rh7 $16) 25... Kxe7 26. Nd5+ Kxe6 27. Nc7+ Kxe5 28. Nxa8 $14 { [#] } 28... Rc6 29. Rd7 (29. a4) 29... Rd6 (29... c4) 30. Rxg7 Rd2+ 31. Kg3 Rxb2 32. Rxg5+ Kd4 33. h4 Rxa2 34. h5 Ra1 $13 { [#] } 35. Kg2 Ra2+ 36. Kg3 Ra1 37. Kg2 Ra2+ 38. Kg1 Ra1+ 39. Kg2 Ra2+ 40. Kg3 Ra1 41. Nc7 c4 42. Ne6+ Ke3 43. Nf4 c3 44. Rc5 Rg1+ 45. Ng2+ Kd3 46. h6 Rh1 47. Nf4+ Kd4 48. Rc6 c2 49. Kg2 Rh4 50. Kg3 Rh1 { 1/2-1/2 The game is a draw. } 1/2-1/2


