isolated pawn is a good thing, like White's d-pawn here which is stopping
Black's from advancing. This advantage in the pawn structure is enough for a
win. (Tarrasch) Finally White has achieved the better position. Black's pawns
are split up and in need of protection. White's pieces are more active.
(Botvinnik 1936) Schwarz hat nun eine ungünstige Bauernstellung: der g-Bauer
verdoppelt, was später von entscheidender Bedeutung wird, und der e-Bauer
