{ Openings Westfield Chatswood NSWJCL event (Saturday and Sunday - blitz)
One-Day, Two-Day Tournaments NSW Junior Championships (analysis) }
1. e4 c5 { Sicilian } 2. Nf3 (2. c3 { Alapin - Black to play (P) } 2... g6!? 3. d4 cxd4 4. cxd4 d5! (4... Nc6 5. d5) 5. e5 (5. exd5 Nf6! 6. Nc3 Nxd5 { Continue with the
Dragon setup }) 5... Bg7 6. Nc3 Nc6 7. Nf3 { Black wants to pressure the d4-pawn
with his pieces (French-style) } (7. Bb5 f6 8. exf6 Nxf6) 7... Bg4 (7... Qb6 8. Nxd5 Qa5+ 9. Nc3) (7... e6 { ...g6 and ...e6 don't mix that well together
(opening) }) 8. Be2 e6 { ...Bg4xf3 and trade a key defender of the d4-pawn }) (2. Nc3 g6 (2... Nc6 3. Bb5!?) 3. f4 Bg7 4. Nf3 { English 'circuit' of tournaments
- Grand Prix (whoever had the most points at the end won) - lot of club
players played this as White in Grand Prix tournaments } 4... Nc6 { Annoying for
Black if he doesn't know what he's doing If Black has a system ready - quite
excited to see this opening (Dragon setup) - ...e6/...d5 } 5. Bc4 { In the
Sicilian - if they play Bc4, ...e6 is a good reply (to kill the bishop) } (5. Bb5 Nd4! 6. Nxd4 cxd4) 5... e6 6. d3 Nge7 7. O-O { Black to play (P) } 7... d5! 8. Bb3 O-O) 2... Nc6 (2... g6!? { Hyper-Accelerated Dragon } 3. c3 Bg7 4. d4 cxd4 5. cxd4 d5) 3. d4 { Open Sicilian } (3. Bb5 { Rossolimo } 3... g6 4. Bxc6 dxc6 { Solid
variation } (4... bxc6 { Sharper approach - Dragon setup (different structure) })) (3. Nc3 g6) 3... cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6 5. Nc3 (5. c4 Bg7) 5... Bg7 6. Be3 (6. Nxc6?! bxc6) 6... Nf6 7. Bc4 { Critical position } (7. f3 O-O 8. Qd2 { Black to play (P) } 8... d5! { If White exchanges, helps Black } 9. exd5 (9. O-O-O dxe4 (9... Re8 10. Bb5) 10. Nxc6 Qxd2+ 11. Bxd2 bxc6 12. fxe4 Bg4) 9... Nxd5 10. Nxc6 bxc6 11. Nxd5 cxd5) 7... O-O 8. Bb3 { Black to play (P) } (8. O-O Nxe4!? 9. Nxe4 d5 { Sicilian Fork Trick }) (8. f3 { Black to play (P) } 8... Qb6 (8... e6 9. Bb3 d5 10. exd5 Nxd5 11. Nxd5 exd5) 9. Bb3 Nxe4! { If White makes one slip he ends up in
serious trouble (material deficit) } 10. Nd5! (10. Nxe4 Bxd4 11. Bxd4 Qxd4 12. Qxd4 Nxd4) (10. Nf5 Nxc3 11. bxc3 Bxc3+) 10... Qa5+ 11. c3 Nf6 12. Nxc6 dxc6 13. Nxe7+ Kh8 14. Nxc8 Raxc8) 8... d6 { Transpose to the Dragon } (8... e5 9. Ndb5 { Outposts for White's knights } 9... d6 10. Qxd6) (8... Re8!?) 9. f3 Bd7 10. Qd2 { Few good choices for Black } 10... Nxd4 11. Bxd4 b5 $10 { Queenside pawn storm
Total Variations: 20 } 0-1


