but to save us having to learn two major variations against the Rubinstein, I
will recommend a shortcut. } (7. Bd2 d5 { transposes to the Rubinstein lines
with Nf3/Bd2, see 4.e3 0-0 5.Nf3. }) 7... Bxc3!? (7... d5 { transposes to the
Rubinstein Main Line, but with 6...b6 7.0-0 Bb7 instead of 6...c5, which I
