you need to be comfortable in Hedgehog type positions after } 8. Na4! cxd4 9. exd4 Re8 10. a3 Bf8 $13 { . }) 8. bxc3 d6 { Black will play very solidly with
...e5 and ...Nc6, and while the engines will claim a tiny edge for White, it
seems very hard to exploit, as both engine and correspondence games have
proved. A key idea is } 9. Nd2 e5 10. e4 Nc6 11. Nb3 Ne7! 12. f3 Ng6 $132 { , rerouting the knight to cover White's kingside ideas and also make the
queenside structure more flexible. }) (4. e3 { This move defines the Rubinstein
