aren't particularly to my taste. }) 6. Qa4+! { wins the bishop! }) 5. Bd3 { The most natural move, keeping the options open. } (5. Nf3 d5 6. Bd2!? { is a somewhat trendy variation, trying to move order Black out of our favoured
Karpov Variation in the main line Rubinstein. But a good reply is } 6... b6 7. Bd3 Bb7 8. cxd5 exd5 9. O-O Bd6! { - this voluntary retreat may seem strange, but
