how your opponents will play } { [%cal Gc1f4] } 7... Nf6 { Defending
against ...Nxe4 - more active way to defend? (P) } { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gd1d3,Gf3g5] } 8. Qd3 (8. Ng5 { [%csl Gf7,Gd7][%cal Ge8g8] } 8... O-O (8... d5 { [%csl Gd5] } 9. exd5 (9. Nxd5 Nxd5 { [%csl Gd5][%cal Ge7g5] }) 9... O-O) 9. e5 Ne8 10. Qh5 { [%csl Gh7] } 10... h6 11. h4 { Fishing Pole } { [%csl Gg5] } 11... hxg5 (11... Bxd4 { [%csl Gg8] } 12. Qg6 { [%csl Gh7][%cal Gc4g8] } 12... hxg5 13. hxg5 { [%cal Gg6h7,Gh1h8] }) 12. hxg5 { [%csl Gh7,Gh8][%cal Gh5h8] }) (8. e5 { if you can play e5 to hit the
f6-knight (no ...d6) } { [%csl Ge5,Gf6][%cal Gd7d6] } 8... Nh5 9. Nd5 { [%csl Ge7][%cal Gd5e7,Gd5f4] }) 8... c6 { [%csl Gc6][%cal Gd7d5] } (8... d6 { Black mainly loses the game
because he doesn't get the pieces out } { [%cal Ge8g8] }) 9. Bxf4 d5 { [%csl Gd5][%cal Ge4d5,Gc4d5,Gc6d5,Gf6d5] } 10. exd5 { [%csl Ge7][%cal Ga1e1,Ge1e8] } 10... O-O 11. d6 Qd8 12. Re1 { f1-king is safe } { [%csl Gf1] } 12... Re8 13. Ng5 { [%csl Gg5,Gf7][%cal Gg8f7] } 13... Rxe1+ 14. Kxe1 Qe8+ 15. Kd2 Be6 16. Re1 { Every piece is involved } { [%csl Gb8,Ga8][%cal Ge1e8] } 16... Nbd7 17. Nxe6 fxe6 18. Rxe6 { 1-0 Black
resigns. } { [%csl Ge8] } 18... Qd8 19. Re8# { [%cal Ge8g8,Gc4g8] } 1-0


