1. e4 { Ernest Morphy (1807-1874) was Paul Morphy's uncle. Ernest had been
referred to as the "Chess King of New Orleans" [see J. Löwenthal's "Morphy's
Games of Chess," p.3]. He was probably also young Paul's greatest admirer.
Besides sending Paul's games to various publications, in Europe as well as in
America, Ernest also tried to arrange matches with the best chess players in
America, though to no avail (erfolglos). The game was played blindfold on
Paul's 12th birthday. Which one played blindfold (or quite possible both), is
not recorded Max Lange:Paul Morphy.3.Aull.1894. Partie 2, S.2-3. Die
anwesenden Zuschauer, meist Angehörige sowie einige Freunde der Familie
Morphy, waren von der kraftvollen Spielweise und sicheren Siegesberechnung des
zwölfjährigen Blindlingsspielers so überrascht, dass sie den Knaben auf
ihren Armen in ein Nebenzimmer trugen, wo sie ihn mit einem bereits für
seinen Geburtstag bereit gehaltenen feingeschnitzten Schachspiel aus Elfenbein
unter wiederholten Beifallsäußerungen beschenkten (Bericht des Augenzeugen
Dr.Ford). } 1... e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. c3 d6 5. O-O Nf6 6. d4 exd4 7. cxd4 Bb6 8. h3 (8. Nc3) 8... h6?! (8... Nxe4 9. Re1 O-O (9... d5 10. Bxd5 Qxd5 11. Nc3) 10. Rxe4 d5 11. Bxd5 Qxd5 12. Nc3) (8... O-O) 9. Nc3 O-O 10. Be3 Re8 11. d5 Bxe3 12. dxc6 Bb6 { [%csl Ga1] } 13. e5 dxe5 { Morphy's style - go for the
beautiful continuation over the simple and good. If we see an attacking idea
and can't see how they defend against it - well worth going on } 14. Qb3? { [%csl Gg8] } (14. Qxd8 Rxd8 15. Nxe5 $14 { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gc4f7] }) 14... Re7 $15 (14... Be6 15. cxb7 Rb8 16. Nxe5) 15. Bxf7+?! (15. Nd5 Nxd5 16. Bxd5 bxc6 17. Bxc6 Rb8 18. Rad1 Qf8 19. Qc3 f6 $15) 15... Rxf7 16. Nxe5 { [%cal Gb3g8] } 16... Qe8 { Pins are all well and good, but we also need back-up to
win material with it } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gb3g8] } 17. cxb7 Bxb7 18. Rae1 { [%cal Ge5f7,Ge8f7] } (18. Qxf7+ Qxf7 19. Nxf7 Kxf7 $17 { Two bishops =
worth about 7 pawns } { [%csl Gb7,Gb6,Gf2,Gf1][%cal Gb6g1,Gb7h1] }) 18... Ba6 $15 (18... Rd8 $17 { [%cal Gd8d1] }) 19. Ng6! { A defence is not easy to find } { [%csl Ge8] } 19... Qd8? (19... Qb8! 20. Re7 Bxf2+ 21. Rxf2 Qxb3 22. axb3 Rb8) (19... Bxf2+! { Look at the checks
and captures } { [%csl Gf2,Ge1] } 20. Kxf2 { Unassuming thinking } { [%csl Ge1,Ge8][%cal Ge1e7] } 20... Rb8 21. Rxe8+ Nxe8+ { Discovered check } { [%cal Gf7f1,Gb8b3] } 22. Kg3 (22. Kg1 Rxb3 23. Rxf7 Kxf7 24. Nh8+ Kg8 25. axb3 Kxh8 $19) (22. Qxf7+ Kxf7 $17 { [%csl Gg6,Gf1] } 23. Ne5+ Ke6 { [%csl Gb2][%cal Gb8b2,Ge6e5,Ga6f1] } 24. Re1 Rxb2+) 22... Rxb3 23. Rxf7 Rxc3+ $19) 20. Re7 { 1-0 Black resigns. } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gb3g8,Gf7g7] } 1-0


