1. e4 { Maroczy: Paul Morphy. Partie 16, S.18. } 1... e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. b4 Bxb4 5. c3 Bc5 6. O-O d6 7. d4 exd4 8. cxd4 Bb6 9. Nc3 Na5 10. Bd3 Bg4 11. Be3 Qf6 12. Nd5 Qd8 13. h3 Bxf3 14. Qxf3 Nf6 { Morphy finds his target and throws
everything at it from this position (wins the game as a result) - winning the
battle for a square can change the whole situation/position to our favour } 15. Bg5 { [%csl Gf6][%cal Gg5d8] } 15... Bxd4 16. e5 Bxe5 17. Re1 { Homework exercise -
defend Black's position (find the best move, or defend against the computer)
(P) } 17... O-O? { Black is castling into danger (is it safe to castle?) } 18. Rxe5! { Black took pieces/material whenever he could } 18... dxe5? 19. Nxf6+ gxf6 { White
has a better move than Bxf6 - puzzle (P) } 20. Bxf6 { 1-0
Black resigns. } { [%cal Gf3g3,Gg3g8] } 20... Qxf6 21. Qxf6 Nc6 { Training position - practice vs. computer/friend - see if you can press
Black from this position } { [%csl Gf7,Ge5,Gf8,Ga8,Gf6,Gg8][%cal Gf6g5] } 1-0


