{ If you want to learn how to play an opening - find master games and play
through them (how a strong player handles the position) }
1. e4 { 1)Daniel Fiske:
The First American Chess Congress New York 1857, p. 223 2)Maroczy: Paul Morphy.
Partie 29, S.33. Theodor Lichtenhein war ein Preuße aus Köngsberg und erst
vor kurzem in die USA gekommen. . } 1... e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Bc4 { SAC - show this opening to the juniors playing } { [%cal Gf1c4,Gc2c3] } 4... Nf6!? { [%csl Ge4,Gd4][%cal Gf6e4] } (4... Bc5) 5. e5 { Black to play (P) } { [%cal Ge5f6] } 5... d5! { Looking for the counterattack against their threat } 6. exf6 (6. Bb5 { [%cal Gb5e8] } 6... Ne4 (6... Nd7) 7. Nxd4 Bd7 { [%cal Gd4c6,Gb5c6] } 8. Nxc6 (8. Bxc6 bxc6 { [%csl Gb5][%cal Gc6b5] } 9. O-O { Bishop pair vs. White's better
pawn structure } { [%csl Gc6,Gc7] } 9... Be7 (9... Bc5 10. Be3 { [%cal Gf2f3,Gf3e4,Gb1c3,Gb1d2] }) 10. f3) 8... bxc6 { White is forced to move his bishop a third time -
White will lose the initiatve } { [%cal Gc6b5] } 9. Bd3 { Morphy was always looking for the way
to attack his opponent } 9... Bc5 { [%csl Gf2][%cal Ge1g1] } (9... Nc5 { [%cal Gc5d3] }) 10. Bxe4 { Easy to assume that e.g. we're forced to automatically recapture
Lasker - 'when you see a good move, look for an even better move' } (10. O-O Qh4 { [%csl Gf2] }) 10... dxe4 (10... Qh4! { [%cal Gh4f2,Gh4e4] } 11. Qe2 dxe4 { [%csl Gd7,Gc5,Gb1,Gc1,Gh4] } 12. Be3 { [%csl Gd8,Gg4][%cal Gc5e3,Ge2e3,Gb1d2] } (12. g3 { [%cal Ge1g1] } 12... Qg4 { [%csl Ge4] }) 12... Bg4! $17 { If we
can keep making threats as Black, White won't have that time to develop his
pieces and castle his king to safety } { [%cal Gg4e2] } 13. Qc4 (13. g3 Qh5 14. Qc4 O-O-O $17) (13. Qd2 { Black to play (P) } { [%csl Ge3,Gd2] } 13... Rd8 14. Qc1 Bxe3 15. Qxe3 Rd1# { [%cal Gd1h1] }) 13... Bxe3 { [%cal Gh4f2,Gc4c6] } 14. g3 { [%csl Gh4] } (14. O-O Bb6 15. Qxc6+ Ke7 $19) (14. Qxc6+ Kf8 (14... Ke7 15. Qxc7+ Ke6 16. Qd6+ Kf5 { [%cal Gd6d7,Gf5g6] } 17. g3 Qh6 { [%cal Gf2e3] } 18. fxe3 (18. Qxh6 Bxh6 { [%csl Gh6,Gg4] }) 18... Qxe3+ 19. Kf1 Bh3#) 15. Qxa8+ Ke7 { [%cal Gh8a8,Gh4f2] } 16. g3 { [%cal Gg3h4,Ga8h8] }) 14... Qd8 $19 { [%cal Gd8d1,Ge3b6] } (14... Qh6! 15. O-O Bc1) (14... O-O-O! { [%cal Gg3h4,Gd8d1] }) 15. fxe3? (15. O-O Bd4) 15... Qd1+ 16. Kf2 { [%csl Gf2] } 16... Qf3+ { [%cal Gf2e1,Gf3h1] } (16... Qxh1 17. Qxc6+ Ke7 { [%cal Ge7e6,Ge6f5] }) 17. Kg1 { [%csl Gh1,Gg1] } 17... Bh3! { [%cal Gf3g2] } 18. Qxc6+ { [%csl Gc6] } 18... Kf8 19. Qxa8+ Ke7 { Time 48 minutes Morphy
hacking his opponent to bits - attacking the king in a very blunt fashion } { [%cal Gf3g2,Gf3f1] })) 6... dxc4 7. fxg7 Bxg7 { [%csl Gd4,Gc4,Gc7,Gb7,Ga7] } 8. Qe2+ Be6 { 0-1 White resigns. } { [%cal Ge6c4] } 0-1


