1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d4 { Morphy: "Lange was the first to maintain
that 4.d4 was stronger than 4.Qe2. In his 'Sammlung neuer Schachpartien' (p.55)
he gives a number of interesting variations on this move." } 4... Nxd4 5. Nxd4 exd4 6. e5 c6 7. O-O (7. exf6 Qa5+) 7... cxb5 8. Bg5 Be7 9. exf6 Bxf6 10. Re1+ Kf8 11. Bxf6 Qxf6 12. c3 { Morphy in Chess Monthly 1959,S.53: "Up to this move the
game coincides with one played by Lange (Schachpartien p56). } (12. Na3 a6 { Max Lange: Paul Morphy. 2.Aufl. S.201: "Auch } 13. Qe2 { bietet eine gute
Fortsetzung, In einer Partie Lange-Anderssen war die Folge" } 13... g6 14. Rad1 Kg7 15. Rd3 d5 16. Rf3? Qd6 (16... Bg4! $19) 17. Qd2 Bf5 18. Qxd4+ f6 19. g4 Bc8 20. Rxf6 { 1-0 } 20... Qxf6 21. Re7+) (12. Qe2 g6 (12... Qe6 13. Qd2 $14) 13. Qxb5 Kg7) 12... d5 13. cxd4 Be6 14. Nc3 a6 15. Re5 Rd8 (15... g6 16. Nxd5 Bxd5 17. Rxd5 Kg7 18. Qd2 Rac8) 16. Qb3 Qe7 17. Rae1 (17. Nxd5 Qd6 $17) 17... g5? (17... Qd6 18. g3 g6) 18. Qd1 (18. Ne2 { /\Ne2-g3-f5/h5 }) 18... Qf6 19. R1e3 { Black to play (P) puzzle - castle 'by hand' } { [%cal Ge1e3] } (19. Ne2) 19... Rg8?? { If you don't see your opponent's threat, you can't really stop it (unless
you got really lucky) } (19... Kg7 { [%csl Gh8][%cal Gf8g7] } 20. Rg3 h6 21. Ne2 (21. h4 g4 { [%csl Gg4] } 22. Rxg4+ Bxg4 23. Qxg4+ { Typical defensive resource
when we're coming under attack - exchange the enemy queen } 23... Qg6 { [%csl Gg4][%cal Gg6g4,Gg4f4] }) 21... Rhg8) (19... Qg6 { [%cal Gf8g7,Gh8e8] }) 20. Rxe6! { 1-0 Black resigns. } { [%cal Gf6e6,Ge3e6] } 20... fxe6 21. Rf3 { [%cal Gf3f8] } 21... Qxf3 22. Qxf3+ { If you miss one big tactic, that can decide the game } { [%csl Gc3] } 1-0


