1. e4 { 1)Lawson: Paul Mprphy. Game 57, p.371. Schulten was an easy prey
(leichte Beute) for Morphy because he was a greedy chess player. "Take and
hold" was his philosophy. Schulten was like the bank - wanting to take all the
money he could (material) } 1... e5 2. f4 d5 (2... exf4 { [%csl Gf4] }) 3. exd5 e4!? { [%csl Gd5] } 4. Nc3 (4. d3 { [%cal Gd3e4] }) 4... Nf6 5. d3 { Want to defend actively } { [%cal Ge4d3,Gf1d3] } 5... Bb4! { [%cal Gb4e1] } 6. Bd2 (6. dxe4 Nxe4 { [%cal Ge4c3,Gd8h4,Gh4e1,Gf6e4] }) 6... e3 { [%cal Gd2e3] } 7. Bxe3 O-O { [%csl Ge1,Gf1,Gg1,Gh1][%cal Gf8e8,Ge8e1] } 8. Bd2 (8. Qd2 Nxd5 9. O-O-O Nxc3 10. bxc3 Ba3+ { [%csl Gb1] } 11. Kb1 { [%csl Gb1][%cal Gd8d5,Gd5b5,Gb5b2] }) 8... Bxc3 9. bxc3 Re8+ 10. Be2 { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gd8d5,Gf6d5] } 10... Bg4! { Very
hard for White to develop normally } { [%cal Ge8e1,Gg4e2] } 11. c4 (11. Nf3 Bxf3 12. gxf3 { [%cal Ge8e1] } 12... Nxd5 13. O-O { [%csl Gg1] } 13... Qh4 { [%csl Gf4,Ge3][%cal Gb8c6,Ge8e6,Ge6g6] }) (11. Kf1 { [%csl Gf1,Ge2,Gg4][%cal Ge8e1] } 11... Bxe2+ 12. Nxe2 Qxd5 { [%csl Gf1] }) 11... c6 12. dxc6? (12. h3) 12... Nxc6 13. Kf1 { Temporary sacrifice to
clear the way for our pin } { [%cal Gg4d1] } 13... Rxe2 $19 { [%cal Gg4d1] } 14. Nxe2 Nd4 { [%csl Ge2][%cal Gg4e2,Gg4d1] } 15. Qb1 Bxe2+ 16. Kf2 { [%csl Gd4,Ge2,Ga1,Gd3,Gc4] } 16... Ng4+ 17. Kg1 Nf3+!! { One tempo very often makes the difference
between checkmating their king and them beating off the attack } { [%cal Gd8d4,Gd4f2] } 18. gxf3 Qd4+ 19. Kg2 Qf2+ { [%csl Gf2,Ge2,Gg4] } 20. Kh3 Qxf3+ { 0-1
White resigns. } { [%csl Ge2,Gf3,Gg4,Gh3] } 21. Kh4 { [%cal Gf2f3] } 21... Ne3 { [%cal Gf3g4] } 22. Qg1 { [%cal Gf3g4] } 22... Nf5+ 23. Kg5 Qh5# { Extra pawn or two is only really going to become valuable
once all the pieces are developed - Develop as rapidly as possible, lead in
development turn into a big attack } 0-1


