{ This was probably my best game in the tournament, which makes it a shame that
I can't remember the brilliant parts. }
1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Nh6! { Aye Carumba! } 6. a3 { [%cal Gb2b4] } 6... f6 { [%csl Ge5] } 7. Bxh6 (7. Bf4 { [%cal Gg7g5] } 7... g5 (7... Nf7 { [%cal Gg5g4,Gf6e5,Gg7g5] })) 7... gxh6 8. exf6 Qxf6 { [%csl Gg7,Gf6][%cal Gf8g7,Ge8g8] } 9. Bd3 (9. dxc5 { [%cal Ge8g8] } 9... Bxc5 { [%cal Ge8g8,Ge6e5,Ge5e4] }) 9... cxd4 10. cxd4 Bg7 { Black is already slightly better. } { [%csl Gd4] } 11. Nc3 (11. Bb5!?) 11... O-O (11... Nxd4 { could be even better although a transposition to the game is more
likely. }) 12. Qc2 Nxd4 13. Nxd4 Qxd4 14. Bxh7+ Kh8 15. O-O Bd7 { From here I
was able to engineer a quick ...e5, and soon after combining the advance of
the central pawns with my kingside attack, my opponent was lost and soon
resigned. } { [%cal Gh7d3,Ge6e5,Ge5e4] } 0-1


