exchange of Q and manages to keep a slight advantage in the endgame thanks to
the extra double-pawn. } 19... Qg5? 20. f4 $16) 17. Qxh6 $16 { /\g4+- The white Q is
misplaced only temporarily, moreover on h6 it can play a role in White's
attack. Also White's K is now quite safe in the middle. } 17... Qf2 (17... Qf6!? 18. Kc2 Nf4 19. Bf1 $16) 18. g4 Nf6 19. Rf1 Qd4+ (19... Qg2 20. Qh4 Kg7 21. g5 (21. Qg3 $16) 21... Nh5 (21... Nh7 22. Qg3! $16) 22. Rf2 Qh3 23. Qxh3 Bxh3 24. f4 $16) 20. Kc2 (20. Qd2?! Qxd2+ 21. Kxd2 g5! $14 { White avoids the
vlack-square blockade and plays for the attack. }) 20... Bd7 21. Rd1 Qf2 22. Nd3! Nxd3 23. Rxd3 Bxa4+? { This sacrifice doen't work due to Black's exposed Q. } (23... c4 24. Rd2 Qc5 25. a5!? b5 26. axb6 Qxb6 27. h4 $40) (23... b5? 24. Rf1 Qg2 25. Rd2 { ףg2 } { [%csl Rg2] }) 24. Rxa4 b5 25. Ra1 b4 26. Rf1 Qg2 27. Qh4! { ףg2 } { [%csl Rg2] } 27... c4 (27... bxc3 28. Rf2 Qg1 29. Rd1 $18) 28. Rd4! (28. Rdd1 Nxe4 29. fxe4 bxc3 $16) 28... Nxe4 (28... bxc3 29. Rf2 $18) 29. fxe4 bxc3 30. Qf2! { 1-0 Black resigns. } (30. Rf2 Qh1) 1-0


