{ I find if you play enough tournaments, there will end up being one bad one
1. Sometimes there are places where I find I don't play that great (Doeberl Cup for me - schedule switches from evening games to morning games)
2. I see it all as part of a journey - enter the games and look toward the next event
3. What positions arose, where did I feel uncomfortable?
- If the next tournament is very close - try to avoid those positions
- If there is more time - work more on those positions before the event
4. Abu Dhabi event 2017 - realised that I had a lot of things going wrong during teh event (laptop crashing, book deadline)
5. Make the decision to accept it and move on }
