6 Be2 a6, lines with early Be3 } 17... Bb7 (17... Na5 18. Qf2 Nc4 19. Bc1 Bb7 20. Nd4 Bf8 21. Nde2 g6 22. b3 Na5 23. Be3 Nc6 24. Rad1 Ba8 25. Rd2 Nb4 { 1/2-1/2 (33)
Fedorchuk,S (2638)-David,A (2579) Saint-Quentin 2014 }) 18. Qf2 Bf8 19. Rad1 { LiveBook: 16 Games. White is slightly better. } 19... Nb4 20. Rd2 Rbd8 $146 (20... Rbc8 21. Rfd1 Qb8 22. Nb1 Rc4 { 0-1 (60) Rosenberger,F (2208)-Stadler,S (2179)
Nuremberg 2004 }) 21. h4 d5 22. e5 Qc4 23. Nd4 Nc6 24. Nce2 Qxa4 25. h5 Nxd4 26. Nxd4 g6 27. Bh3 { [%mdl 1024] White has compensation. } 27... Nc5 28. Qh4 Re7 29. Rh2 Rde8 30. Bg4 Bc8 31. Qh3 Ra7 32. c3 a5 33. Rg1 Qd7 34. Rd1 Rc7 35. Bg1 Bb7 36. Bf3 Qa4 37. Be2 Ree7 (37... Ba6! { keeps the balance. } 38. hxg6 fxg6) 38. Be3 (38. Re1 $16) 38... Ba6 39. Bg4 Kh8 40. Kg1 Bc8 41. Nc2 Ba6 42. Bd4 Qc6 43. Kh1 Bb5 44. Bg1 Ba4 45. Nd4 Qe8 46. Re1 Bd7 47. Be2 a4 48. Ra1 Qb8 49. Nc2 Nb3 50. Rd1 Qb7 { next ...d4+ is good for Black. } 51. Nd4 b5 52. Nxb3 axb3 53. Rd4 Qa8 54. Bd3 Be8 55. Rg2 Ra7 56. Kh2 (56. Rb4) 56... Ra1 $15 57. Kg3 Qc8! 58. Be2 Rc7 59. Kh2 Kg8 60. Rd1 Rxd1 61. Bxd1 b4 62. hxg6 hxg6 63. cxb4 Rb7 64. Kg3 { Black must now prevent Rh2. } 64... Rxb4 { aiming for ...Qc1. } 65. Rh2 { [%csl Gh2][%cal Rh3h8] } 65... Bg7 66. Qg2 Bb5 67. Qd2 Bf8! 68. Be3 Qc4 69. Be2 Qc6 70. Bd1 Re4 71. Bf3 Ra4 72. Qd1 Bc4 73. Qh1 { White wants to mate with Rh8+. } 73... Bg7 74. Qc1 Qb7 75. Qc3 Qb5 76. Rh1 Bf8 77. Bd4 Ra8 78. Qd2 Bd3! 79. Be3 Ra4 80. Qh2 { [%csl Gh1][%cal Rh2h8] } 80... Bg7 81. Qh7+ Kf8 82. Qh2 Bc2 83. Qd2 Kg8! 84. Rc1 Bf8 85. Rh1 Qa5 { And now ...Qxd2 would win. } 86. Qh2 { [%csl Gh1][%cal Rh2h8] } 86... Bg7 87. Qh7+ Kf8 88. Qh2 Qb4 89. Qf2 (89. Qg1 $17 { was called for. } 89... Kg8 90. Qc1) 89... d4 $19 90. Bd2 Qc5! 91. Qe1 Kg8 92. Rh2 Qc4 93. Qc1 Bd3 94. Qxc4 Rxc4 95. Ba5 Bf5 96. Rd2 { [#] } 96... Bf8! 97. Bd1 { [#] } (97. Bg4) 97... Rc2! { [%mdl
512] } 98. Rf2 (98. Bxc2 bxc2) 98... Rc1 99. Bxb3 d3 100. Bd2? (100. Rd2 Rg1+ 101. Rg2) 100... Rg1+ 101. Rg2 Rf1 102. Rf2 { [#] } 102... Ra1! 103. Be3 (103. Kf3 Rh1 104. Bc4) 103... Bb4 104. Kf3 Rg1 105. Rg2 Rf1+ 106. Rf2 Rh1 { Hoping for ...
Rh3+. } 107. Rg2 Be1 { ( -> ...Rh3+) } 108. Bf2 Rf1 109. Ke3 { intending Bxe1. } 109... d2 110. Ba4 (110. Ke2 Rh1 111. Ba4) 110... Bxf2+ { Black is clearly winning. } 111. Ke2 (111. Rxf2 d1=Q 112. Bxd1 Rxd1 113. Rd2 Re1+ 114. Re2) 111... Ra1 112. Rxf2 Rxa4 113. Kxd2 { [%mdl 4096] Endgame KRB-KR } 113... Rc4 114. Ke3 Rc2 115. Rf1 Rxb2 116. Kd4 Rb1 117. Rf2 Rd1+ 118. Kc5 Kf8 119. Rb2 { Precision: White = 59%, Black =
