1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. e5 Nfd7 5. f4 c5 6. Nf3 Nc6 7. Be3 Be7 (7... a6 8. Qd2 b5 9. Nd1 { Smirnov-Illingworth, NSW Open 2015 } { [%csl Gd3,Gb2,Gc3,Gd4,Ge5,Gg1][%cal Gc2c3,Gf1d3,Ge1g1] }) 8. Qd2 O-O 9. Be2 a6 10. O-O b5 11. a3 Qb6 12. Nd1 a5 13. c3 a4 { [%cal Gb5b4,Gd4c5] } (13... Bb7 { White to play (P) } { [%cal Gb5b4] } 14. Rb1 (14. Bd3 { Kingside attack with f5 } { [%csl Gd1,Gf2][%cal Gf4f5,Gf5e6,Gd1f2] } 14... b4 15. f5 { [%cal Gd1f2] }) 14... b4 { [%cal Gb4a3,Gb2a3,Gb6b1] } 15. Nf2) (13... Ba6 14. dxc5 Bxc5 15. b4 Bxe3+ 16. Nxe3 { - good structure for White - strong grip on dark squares in the centre } { [%csl Gb5,Ga6,Gc5,Gb4,Gd4][%cal Gf3d4] }) 14. Nf2 Ba6 15. Nd3 { [%csl Gb4,Gc5][%cal Gb5b4] } 15... Rfc8 16. dxc5 Nxc5 { [%cal Gd3c5,Gc5b3,Gc5e4] } 17. Nxc5 Bxc5 18. Bxc5 Qxc5+ 19. Kh1 Na5 20. Nd4 Nc4 { [%cal Gd5c4] } 21. Bxc4 (21. Qc1 { - dream position for White strategically (when the a6-bishop is so bad, Black has no pawn break) } { [%cal Gf7f6,Gd4e6] }) 21... dxc4 22. Rae1 Rd8 23. f5 exf5 24. Qg5 h6 25. Qxf5 Ra7 26. Qf3 Rf8 27. e6 Bc8 28. Nc6 Bb7 29. Qxf7+ Rxf7 30. exf7+ Kh7 31. Nxa7 Bxg2+ 32. Kxg2 Qg5+ 33. Kf3 Qf5+ 34. Ke3 Qd3+ 35. Kf4 Qd6+ 36. Re5 g6 37. Kg4 Qxe5 38. f8=Q Qh5+ 39. Kg3 Qg5+ 40. Kh3 Qh5+ 41. Kg2 Qd5+ 42. Qf3 Qd2+ 43. Kh1 { 1-0 Black resigns. } 1-0


