1. e4 c5 2. c3 e6 3. d4 d5 4. exd5 exd5 5. Nf3 { - you have a few decent options as Black } { [%cal Ga7a6] } 5... Nc6 6. Bb5 Bd6 7. dxc5 Bxc5 { [%cal Ge8g8] } 8. O-O Ne7 9. Nbd2 O-O 10. Nb3 Bb6 $10 { Karpov-Kortschnoj (Korchnoi) World Championship Matches - Black was holding his own in these IQP positions } { [%csl Gf5,Gg4][%cal Gd8d6,Ga8d8,Gc8g4,Gf8e8] } 11. h3 Bf5 12. Nbd4 Be4 13. Be3 Qd6 14. Re1 Rad8 15. Nd2 Nxd4 16. Bxd4 Bxd4 17. cxd4 Bg6 18. Qb3 a6 19. Bd3 Nc6 20. Nf3 Bxd3 21. Qxd3 Rfe8 22. a3 h6 23. Re3 Re6 24. Rxe6 fxe6 25. Re1 Rf8 26. Qb3 Rf7 27. Qe3 Re7 28. Re2 Re8 29. Qd3 Rf8 30. Qe3 Re8 31. Re1 Re7 32. Nh4 Rf7 33. Qxe6 Qxe6 34. Rxe6 Nxd4 35. Rd6 Ne2+ 36. Kf1 Nf4 37. Ng6 Nxg6 38. Rxg6 Rc7 39. Rb6 Kf7 40. g4 Ke7 41. Ke2 Kd7 42. Kd3 Kc8 43. Rd6 Rf7 44. Ke3 Re7+ 45. Kf3 Re5 46. Rg6 Re7 47. Rd6 Re5 48. h4 Kc7 49. Rg6 Re7 50. h5 d4 51. g5 d3 52. gxh6 d2 53. Rg1 Re1 54. Rxg7+ Kc6 55. Rg6+ Kd7 56. Rg7+ Ke6 57. Rg6+ Kf7 58. Rd6 d1=Q+ 59. Rxd1 Rxd1 { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


