1. e4 c5 2. c3 e6 3. d4 d5 4. e5 Nc6 5. Nf3 Qb6 (5... Bd7 { [%cal Gf7f6,Gf6e5] }) 6. Be2 (6. a3 { [%cal Gb2b4,Gg8h6] } 6... f6!? { Unusual but quite good } { [%cal Gc5d4,Gf6e5,Gb2b4] } 7. b4 (7. Bd3 fxe5 8. Nxe5 { [%cal Gg8f6,Gc6e5] } 8... Nf6 { e5-outpost, but we have a central majority and nice development } { [%csl Ga3][%cal Gf8d6,Ge8g8,Gb2b4] }) 7... fxe5 (7... c4 { [%csl Ge5] }) 8. dxc5 (8. dxe5 c4 { Nh6-f7/g6/Bg7 - e5 is a weak pawn } { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gg8h6,Gh6f7,Gg7g6,Gf8g7,Gb6c7] }) 8... Qc7 $13 { [%csl Ge5,Gd5,Ge6][%cal Ge5e4,Gg8f6,Gf8e7,Ge8g8] }) 6... Nh6 7. O-O (7. b3 { [%csl Gd4] } 7... cxd4 8. cxd4 Nf5 9. Bb2 Bb4+ { [%csl Gc3][%cal Gb1d2,Gc6d4] } 10. Kf1 { [%cal Gf6e5] } 10... f6 $10 { If you can't win their d4-pawn - then ...f6 works well to destroy their centre } { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gf6e5,Gd4e5] }) 7... cxd4 8. cxd4 Nf5 { White would be losing a pawn } { [%csl Gd4] } *


