1. e4 e6 { If you do want to play the French (surprise weapon) - important to practice it in some games beforehand (Lichess or Chess.com) } 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 { [%csl Gb4][%cal Ge4e5] } 4. Bg5 Bb4 5. e5 (5. exd5) 5... h6 { [%cal Gg5e3,Gg5c1] } 6. Bd2 { Model game for McCutcheon } 6... Bxc3 7. bxc3 (7. Bxc3 Ne4 { [%cal Ge4c3,Gc7c5] }) 7... Ne4 8. Qg4 { Black has to weaken your kingside } { [%cal Ge8f8,Gg7g6] } 8... Kf8 { [%csl Gc3,Gc2][%cal Ge1d2] } 9. Bd3 Nxd2 10. Kxd2 c5 { Black's plan is - ...c4, ...b5, ...a5 and ...b4 } { [%cal Gc5c4,Gb7b5,Ga7a5,Gb5b4] } 11. h4 c4 12. Be2 Nc6 13. Nh3 b5 14. a3 a5 15. Nf4 Rg8 16. Rh3 Ne7 { Rg8 stops Rg3/Qg4 battery
Ne7 - Rg3 with Nf5
- looks weird/passive, but it's quite hard for White to break through on the kingside } { [%cal Gh3g3,Ge7f5,Gc8d7,Gd7e8,Ge8f7,Ga8b8,Gb5b4] } 17. h5 Rb8 18. Bd1 Ke8 19. Ne2 Nc6 20. Qf4 Qe7 21. Qe3 Kd8 22. f4 Kc7 23. g4 b4 24. axb4 axb4 25. cxb4 Qxb4+ 26. Qc3 Qxc3+ 27. Kxc3 Bd7 28. g5 Ra8 29. Rxa8 Rxa8 30. Kb2 Ne7 31. Ra3 Rxa3 32. Kxa3 Nf5 33. c3 Ne3 34. Ba4 Bxa4 35. Kxa4 Kb6 36. Kb4 Ng4 37. Ng3 g6 38. gxh6 Nxh6 39. hxg6 fxg6 40. Ka4 Ng4 41. Ne2 Nf2 42. f5 gxf5 43. Nf4 Ne4 44. Nxe6 Nxc3+ 45. Kb4 Ne2 46. Ng7 Nxd4 47. e6 Nc6+ 48. Kc3 Ne7 49. Kd4 Kc7 { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


