1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 (2... e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6 { - not putting pressure on the centre at all (...Qc7/...Bb4) } { [%csl Gc3] } 5. c4 { [%cal Gb1c3,Gf1e2,Ge1g1] }) 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 (4... e6 5. Nc3 Qc7 { [%csl Gc7,Gb5,Ge7,Gc5,Gb4][%cal Ga7a6,Gg8f6] } 6. Be3 a6 7. Qf3 { DTS } (7. Qd2 { Houdini-Komodo (Komodo made lots of positional mistakes) })) (4... g6 5. c4) 5. Nc3 e6 { Accelerated Dragon & Four Knights Sicilian highest strike rate below 2000 Elo
English Attack doesn't work against quite a few systems (Kan/Four Knights)
Move 5 - what's different about their setup? } { [%cal Gc1e3,Gd1d2,Gf2f3,Ge1c1] } 6. Be3 (6. Ndb5 Bb4 7. a3 Bxc3+ 8. Nxc3 d5 { Dismantling the Sicilian (2017 edition) }) (6. Nxc6 bxc6 7. e5 Nd5 8. Ne4 { - play the most ambitious line, often we'll get a much better position (see games in file) } 8... Qc7 9. f4 Qb6 10. c4 { White is better } { [%csl Gd6,Gd5][%cal Ge1e2,Ge2f3] }) 6... Bb4 { I'm not
certain if I've already made the mistake or if I just don't know the correct
way to play the position from here. But I've been here before and either
accepted a wrecked pawn structure, or just lost the pawn (more so in rapid). } { [%csl Ge3,Gd4] } 7. f3 { What is Black's dream Sicilian break? } { [%cal Gd7d5] } (7. Bd3 d5 8. Nxc6 bxc6 9. e5 { [%csl Gd5,Gc6][%cal Gf6d7,Gd1g4,Gd5d4] } 9... Nd7) 7... Qa5 (7... d5! { [%cal Gf1b5,Gd4c6] } 8. Nxc6 bxc6 9. e5 { [%cal Gf3f4] }) 8. Nxc6 (8. Qd2 { [%csl Gd6,Gc7,Ge5][%cal Gd4b3,Gb4c3,Gd2c3] } 8... d5 9. Nb3 { [%cal Ga5c7] }) 8... bxc6 (8... Bxc3+ 9. bxc3 Qxc3+ 10. Bd2 Qxc6 11. Bb4 { [%cal Gb4f8] } 11... d5 { [%cal Ga2a4,Gf1b5] } 12. a4 a6 13. e5 { [%csl Gf6][%cal Gf3f4] } 13... Nd7 14. f4) 9. Bd2 { f3/f4 only be a good move when you can cover the diagonal with Be3 } { [%csl Ge3] } (9. Qd2 { [%csl Gc3] }) 9... Qc7 10. Bd3 d5 { Keep a central pawn } 11. exd5 (11. O-O { [%csl Gd5,Ge4] } 11... O-O 12. Qe2 $10 { [%cal Ge4e5,Gf3f4,Ga1e1] }) 11... exd5 (11... cxd5 12. Nb5) 12. Qe2+ Be6 13. O-O O-O 14. Nxd5?? { No, I'm not winning a pawn... I'm losing a piece. } { Kh1 is an automatic move } { [%csl Gg1][%cal Gc6d5,Gb6g1] } (14. Kh1 { [%cal Gb6g1] } 14... Rfe8 15. Qf2 { Scotch Four Knights (good version for Black) } { [%csl Gc5][%cal Ga1e1,Gc3a4] } 15... Be7 { [%cal Gc6c5,Gc5c4,Gf3f4,Gf4f5] }) 14... cxd5 (14... Nxd5 { [%cal Gd2b4,Gd5b4] }) 15. Bxb4 Qb6+ { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


