{ King's Gambit, other favourite openings? }
1. e4 { Can you read this message? } 1... d6 (1... Nf6 { [%cal Gd2d4,Gf6e4] } 2. e5 { [%cal Gd2d4] } 2... Nd5 3. d4 { Alekhine's Defence }) 2. Nf3 (2. d4 { If they can't take on d4 or e4, this is absolutely a good move (taking the full centre) - dream centre } { [%csl Ge4] }) 2... e5 { Philidor Defence } 3. d3 { King's Gambit, Scandinavian, and Queen's Gambit Declined } { [%csl Gd4][%cal Gd3d4,Gd4e5] } (3. d4! { Line-opening move - attacking the e5-pawn, opening up the lines for our c1-bishop and queen.
The Initiative - like the ball in soccer. Control of the game. It's how we win.
The Initiative is when we have a good flow of threats - not just one or two but several threats in a row to our opponent. } { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gc1h6,Gd1d8,Gd4e5] }) 3... Be6 { We don't know the best square for the bishop } { [%csl Gc1,Gd2,Ge3,Gg5] } (3... Nf6 { In general it's better to develop your knights before your bishops }) 4. Be3 (4. Nc3 { [%cal Gc3d5] }) (4. Be2 { Prepare castling } { [%cal Gf1e2,Ge1g1] }) 4... Be7 5. Be2 d5 { White to play (puzzle) } { [%csl Gd5,Ge5,Ge4,Gd3][%cal Ge4d5] } 6. exd5 Bxd5 7. O-O Nf6 8. Qd2 (8. Nc3) 8... O-O 9. Nc3 Ng4 10. Rad1 Nc6 11. Rfe1 Bb4 12. a3 Bxc3 13. bxc3 (13. Qxc3) 13... Qd6 14. Nh4 e4 15. dxe4 Qxh2+ *


