1. e4 { Can you read this message? } 1... d6 2. Nf3 e5 3. d3 (3. d4) 3... Be6 4. Be3 Be7 5. Be2 d5? { White to play (Puzzle) - 2nd World Champion Emanuel Lasker - when you see a good move, look for an even better one. - are the pieces safe? } 6. exd5 (6. O-O { [%cal Ge1g1] }) (6. Nxe5 { [%csl Ge5] } 6... Bf6 { [%cal Gf6e5] } 7. Bf4 { [%csl Ge5] } (7. Nf3 { What pieces are undefended? - great way to spot tactics } 7... Bxb2 { John Nunn - LPDO - Loose Pieces Drop Off } { [%csl Gb2][%cal Gb2a1] } 8. Nbd2 Bxa1 9. Qxa1 { Pawn = 1 Knight = 3.25 Bishop = 3.5 Rook = 5 Queen = 9.75. Black won 1.5 pawns worth of material } { [%csl Gh8,Gf8] })) 6... Bxd5 7. O-O (7. Nxe5 Bxg2 { [%csl Gg2] } 8. Rg1 Bd5 { White to play (Puzzle) - grab a pawn } { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gg1g7] } 9. Rxg7 Bf6 { Fork - } { [%csl Gf7,Ge5][%cal Gd5f7,Ge8f7] } 10. Rg1 Bxe5) 7... Nf6 (7... Nc6 { [%cal Gc6e5,Gc3d5] } 8. Nc3 { Bishop is slightly better than the knight on average. - the broader the battlefield (pawns on both sides) - the better the bishop will be over the knight. If it's a very closed position - then the knights can easily be better. } { [%csl Ge3,Gg8][%cal Gc3d5] } 8... Nf6 9. Nxd5 Nxd5 { [%cal Gd5e3] }) 8. Qd2 (8. Nc3) (8. Nxe5 { Are their/my pieces safe? - ask on every move } { [%cal Gd5g2,Gg1g2] }) 8... O-O (8... Nc6 { e5-pawn is protected. Not enough to occupy the centre with pawns - we also should control the centre with pieces } { [%cal Gc6e5,Gf3e5] }) 9. Nc3 Ng4 { Moving the same piece twice } { [%cal Gg4e5] } (9... Nc6 { Defending e5 and developing a new piece. Good chess moves do several things at once. }) 10. Rad1 Nc6 11. Rfe1 { Rooks belong in the centre (at least if the centre is somewhat open) } 11... Bb4 (11... Nxe3 { Knight for Bishop }) 12. a3 Bxc3 13. bxc3 { Recapture toward the centre - improves central control. Doubled c-pawns } { [%csl Ga3,Gc3,Gc2] } (13. Qxc3! { [%cal Gb2c3] } 13... Nxe3 14. fxe3 { Flexible structure } { [%cal Ge3e4,Gd3d4] }) 13... Qd6 14. Nh4 { Tactics will decide games. - solve tactics puzzles } 14... e4 { Are the pieces safe? White to Play (Puzzle) } { [%csl Ge4,Ge5][%cal Ge5e4] } 15. dxe4 Qxh2+ *


