1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. Nf3 Nb6 7. Nc3 Nc6 8. e3 O-O 9. O-O Re8 10. Re1 a5 11. Qd2?! { A very strange move. I still believe
that it was a "lapsus manus": Carlsen intended to play the theoretical } (11. Qe2) 11... e5 12. d5 Nb4 13. e4 c6 14. a3 cxd5! { Quite an obvious refutation
of White's play. } 15. axb4 axb4 16. Rxa8 bxc3 17. bxc3 Nxa8 18. exd5?! (18. Qxd5 Nb6 (18... Qxd5 19. exd5 Nb6 20. Nd2) 19. Qa5 { although Black,
controlling the crucial c4-square, keeps a small edge after } 19... Qf6 20. Bg5 Qc6) 18... Nb6 19. Rd1?! (19. d6 Re6 (19... Nc4!?)) (19. c4!? Nxc4 20. Qb4 Nd6 21. Be3 { getting some activity for the missing pawn although Black is
obviously better. }) 19... e4 20. Ng5?? { Just blundering a piece in a poor
position. } (20. Ne1 Bg4 21. f3 e3 22. Qe2 Bd7 23. Bxe3 (23. c4 Nxc4! 24. Qxc4 e2 25. Rd2 Qb6+ 26. Kh1 Qf2 $19) 23... Ba4 24. Rd2 Bxc3 $19) (20. Nh4 h6 $19) (20. Nd4 Qxd5 $19) 20... e3 21. Qb2 Qxg5 22. Bxe3 (22. Qxb6 e2 23. Re1 Qxc1 24. Rxc1 e1=Q+ 25. Rxe1 Rxe1+ 26. Bf1 Bh3 $19) 22... Qg4 { 0-1 White resigns. } (22... f3 23. Nc4) 0-1


