1. a3 a6 { Since 1.e4 didn't offer any edge at all because of 1...c5, let's consider 1.d4. } 2. d4 d5 3. Bf4 (3. c4?! dxc4! 4. Nf3 b5 $15 { White needs to play a3-a4, giving Black the advantage. }) (3. Nf3 Bf5! 4. e3 e6 5. c4 Nf6 6. Nc3 h6 $10 { [%cal Gd1b3,Ga8a7] }) 3... c5! 4. dxc5 (4. e3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Bg4! $10 { [%cal Gf1b5] }) (4. c3 Nf6 5. e3 e6 6. Nd2 b5!? 7. Ngf3 Bb7 $10) 4... e6 5. e3 Bxc5 6. c4 Nf6 7. Nf3 O-O { Black is a tempo up on the Blackburne QGD after } { [%cal Ga2a3,Ga7a6] } 8. Nc3 (8. cxd5 Nxd5 9. Bg3 b5 $10) *


