1. a3 a6 2. c4!? e6 (2... b5? 3. e4 bxc4 4. Bxc4 $16) (2... c6 3. e3 (3. d4 d5 4. e3 Bf5 5. Nf3 e6 6. Nc3 Nd7 7. Bd3 Bxd3 8. Qxd3 Ngf6 9. O-O Be7 10. e4 dxe4 11. Nxe4 O-O 12. Bf4 { White has the better side of equality. Perhaps that's the most he can hope for against the Slav with a3/a6 inserted. }) 3... d5 4. Nf3 Bf5! $10 5. Qb3 Ra7 (5... b5)) (2... e5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. e3! d5 6. d4 exd4 7. exd4 $14 { ...a6 is a bit pointless here. } { [%csl Gc6] }) (2... c5 3. Nc3 Nc6 4. Nf3 (4. e3 Nf6 5. d4 cxd4 6. exd4 d5 7. Nf3 Bg4 8. cxd5 Nxd5 9. Qb3? Bxf3 10. gxf3 Nxd4 11. Qxb7 Rb8 $17) 4... Nf6 5. d4 cxd4 6. Nxd4 g6 7. e4 Nxd4 8. Qxd4 d6 $14 { ...a6 more useful than a3 in the Bind }) (2... Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. e4 d6 5. d4 Bg7 6. Nf3 O-O 7. Be2 (7. h3!? c5 8. d5 e6 9. Bd3 exd5 10. exd5 (10. cxd5 b5 11. O-O Re8 $10) 10... b5! $10) 7... e5 8. d5! $14 { Best move is 8...a5, but costs a tempo } { [%cal Ga6a5] }) 3. d4 d5 (3... Nf6 4. Nc3 d5 5. cxd5 exd5 6. Bg5 c6 7. e3 Bf5 8. Qf3 Bg6 9. Bxf6 Qxf6 10. Qxf6 gxf6 11. Nf3 Nd7 12. Nh4 Be7 13. Ne2 $14 { [%cal Ge7b4] }) 4. e3 Nf6 5. Nf3 dxc4 6. Bxc4 c5 7. O-O $10 { Harmless sideline of QGA } *


